\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And that was it was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That was - that was it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did anybody else besides your parents and your brothers and sisters live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your mother have anybody to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 She used to have a - a lady for to help her wash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was that once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Monday morning. Once a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did she do anything else at all apart from helping with the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That's the only thing she did was help - was helping with washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Your mother worked with the washing as well did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Me mother helped her kind of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 They did it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did you get on with this person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well very - very well. Me mother had known her for - she was a young girl and they had a fruit shop and their name were called Liptro
t in Bridgeman Street, her husband were a cripple and she used just come and help me mother and me mother used give her half a crown and a dinner and they'd have to get through the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did she show any interest in the members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well we always like spoke to her as our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 auntie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 , we called her our - you know, you're auntie, with know, she'd know'd us all being brought up and we always called her Auntie Meg. That was her - what we called her. Her real name was Mrs Liptrot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did she call you, she would call you by your Christian name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Oh yes, call me William, Billy and me brothers John and Jim and - she were right friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did your mother and she call each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well me mother always called her w
ith her - call this lady, call her with her first name. She never used call her Mrs Liptrot in front of us, it were always Annie or something like that, you know, what her real name was, I couldn't just tell you know her real name, like what you called he
r by but it was always her Christian name, she was called by kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did she call your mother Mrs Burtonwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, she always used call me mother - her - her own name like. She were called Sarah Anne me mother and she used always say like S
arah Anne to her, I can remember that quite well. There were nobody any - above one another. We were all on - they were all classed on same level kind of thing, that's what I mean say. We weren't over her and she weren't - over us. We were all on one foot
ing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So there was just the washing that your mother had help with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That's all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your mother or father mend or make any of the family's clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did she - did he what - ever - oh yes, oh yes. We had to have 'em. And there were 
a lot of them handed down. Oh yes, I wore - I wore me brother's clothes sometimes. But I always had a Sunday suit. And so had me brothers and me sisters Sunday clothes and they were Sunday clothes. There were no putting them on during week, Saturday night
.
 You only put 'em on at Sunday if you were going anywhere special with your mother and father but never on again. After Sunday school they were off and put away. Now that's one thing what I've always brought my family up to do. But you can't get it done t
oday. I still class my Sunday clothes, me best clothes as me Sunday suit and I only where it at - on special occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was it your mother who made your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 She used to make some of them and - and buy some, you know, like - she did a lot of 
her own kitting, knitting our stockings and that. Me dad's, whole family but she used to buy a lot of our clothes like and - and mend a lot and they were mended when they were - when they were being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 thrown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  away they were - they'd had their use.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When she bought clothes where would she buy them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well she were a big member of stores, that were at time when divi were three and three in't pound. And it - a lot came from the stores, biggest majority.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did she ever have to buy any secondhand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well I can't answer you that question because I can never remember her ever buying any, she'd probably have had some clothes give off - give her to - off me aunties and me uncles, they might have handed some down, well - well you Sarah - you S
arah Anne use these or what. She might have done but I can't answer you that question truthful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 About how often would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well we used to have make our clothes do about two year and when we got a new suit it had to last us two 
year and then that suit as what we had what was not using, we went to day school in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You mean what had been your Sunday suit then became your everyday suit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Going to school. But at Holiday times you didn't wear that suit at holiday times when
 you were on holidays from school. You had some more old'ns, you had to wear them, same as at Saturday, you didn't put your school - what you went school in, you had these old'ns because me mother and father were strict. In fact, sometimes I think they we
re too strict but it's done me no harm with her being strict with me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about shoes, did your mother buy those for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes, and then I had me oldest sister, she were manageress of a boot shop, Morris's in Newport Street and - she used bring 
us our shoes and we'd get 'em a - a little bit cheaper, that's when she become manageress in this shop in - Morris's it were called in Newport Street. We got a lot of our shoes through me sister from Morris's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your father ever do any cobbling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes. Our clogs. And - he used to clog 'em himself and iron 'em. A set of irons if you went to cobblers then was tuppence ha'penny and you could get 'em from ironmongers, Knowsleys in Fletcher Street, you could get a set for three ha'pence and do 'em 
yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever mend your ordinary shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes, yes. Did biggest majority of our mending of me shoes - of our family's shoes bar when they were getting a bit bigger, me sisters. He didn't tackle them like, they weren't good enough for him to - have 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When they were becoming fashion conscious you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That kind of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 About how often did you have new shoes when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well when we got our new suit we got a new rig-out completely everything. Stocki
ngs and all the lot, shirts and everything. But we never our shirts when I was getting older I wore a collar and tie and I never had a white shirt at Sunday 'til I were about eighteen year old. I used to have one what they used call a dicky at front and i
t fastened on with your collar and on elastic at back and you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 fastened}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 it on your braces and you thought you had a Sunday shirt on but you only had your ordinary everyday shirt on. I don't know whether you know anything about that but that's what we used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your father used to help your mother in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Not a lot. It was just me sisters and brother. Me sisters used to do a lot, helping but - not me dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he do anything at all, cleaning, cooking, washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Me dad? Sunday
 mornings breakfast. And that was cooked at front at fire on toasting fork. Bacon, tripe, meat - it were a real fry up at front of fire. And on toasting forks then, you might not have seen any of these things but it were at front of your fire and some of 
bars fell down your plate were there and then you had a two bar and you shove your - and all the fat was dropping all on - that were your father's plate and he dished it out at Sunday morning, that'd the only thing I can ever remember him doing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever make the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was that one of his jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 One of his jobs at - was beating fire before he went work and they used start at six o'clock at morning then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever do any decorating or repairs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well, no, not as I can bring to mind. I never knowed him do any - any beautifying or anything like that. Because he were never interested in it, he were more interested in iron that doing any - any beautifying and in them days it were mostly painting wha
t was being done you know and - and whitewashing. You was very lucky if your - when you had your front room papered, your back kitchen might have been where your sink was, might have been just whitewashed or kind of distemper on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your father ever do anything for the children like dressing or undressing or bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 
Well at Saturday night - when we was, you know, on - well, young, we used - they used - I can remember 'em starting off with me sisters, we might be out playing, and then lads ha
d to come in hot water with tin bath in front of fireplace, he'd give me mother a lift with them then as they were bathed they were upstairs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh he used help a bit like getting jobs done like in getting kids out of road so they could have a quiet night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well he did a bit and - he didn't kind of thing. You used - if we wanted know anything we'd go and ask him, he were a sensible fellow like that. If you were - he always used tell us, if we w
ere having any trouble we had go to him or go to me mother and they'd sort it out between 'em, you understand. Like, but he always made sure we were always in bed before nine o'clock. That was his way of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever take you out without your mother? Or look after you while she went out
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
No. Saturday nights we'd go and have a tramcar ride up to Crown Hotel, that's up Chorley New Road. Me and me other brother and me sister because the others were a bit too big then to go with us and we'd go up
 to Crown Hotel. Me mother and me dad'd just go and have a drink and then would come out and we'd walk part way home and then ride t'other part way home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have any jobs to carry out regularly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, I never had a job at home. Only 
going errands like, I had to go errands like for me mother. I had to go errands for her but I never had a stipulated job was my job to do. Like if they said, bring some coal well you just went and brought some coal. But chopping firewood or anything like 
that, I never - I can't remember ever chopping any. It was always there when I wanted it - now who }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 chopped}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 it up I can't tell you, I think it might have been me dad or me brothers, but I don't think me mother ever chopped any up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can you remember if your brothers or sisters did have jobs assigned to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Only - after teatime when they'd started working. They used wash up and help me mother and do their own bedrooms. And - me mother looked after our bedrooms but me sister used - me sisters looked 
after their own. 'Cos two of me sisters were older than lot of us you understand. And they - were a little bit - they were getting like in womanhood kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 It was just your sisters that helped in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Not your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. Just me sisters what did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your older brothers and sisters help you at all with things like dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, I can't remember 'em ever helping me or showing me anything because - as - when we were at home having our meals
 we was always all at table and - me mother and father used - if I were going wrong anywhere I was quickly pulled up with me mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you do anything to help your older brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I - I'd go errands for 'em, probabl
y I'd go an errand and they'd give me ha'penny but I always used get that off me sisters and brothers when they were working, I used get a ha'penny a week off 'em when they got their spending money. That were one of me dad's always said, well, our Billie'
s not working so - you'll have to give him a ha'penny }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 apiece}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 out of your spending money. And that were my spending money off me sisters and brothers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did that start from when your oldest started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Started working. As they started working and they brought their first wage in I got a ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about the ones in between - did they get anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well it'd always - it'd always run in't family as when we me oldest sister started working she gave ha'penny to next 'n you see, and t
hen when next 'n come on she started working, she give ha'penny to that one and then that one give ha'penny on and it was followed on. You see. But when it came to my turn I was getting a matter of tuppence ha'penny a week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 You see, they were all working and me being youngest of family they were all taking a bit of sympathy on me and giving me a ha'penny apiece and I got three ha'pence off me dad and a penny of me mother. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Now that mine - that were mine for the week then. And probably I might, if me mother a
sked me go an errand she might give me ha'penny, or say buy a ha'orth of toffees. That were it. And I reckon when I were a youngster I had a - I had a good life. I had a strict life. You understand? I had to go to Sunday school morning, afternoon and - me
 father didn't go but he always made sure - all me sisters and brothers went. We had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Your mother and father together put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Or was it your mother during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Mother, me mother during week. Me father supervised
, as soon as he saw clock going round half past eight we were all making shine ready for bed. Even me sister at nineteen year old had to be in during week at nine o'clock. And Sat'day night they got 'til half past nine. And when I were twenty-one I used g
e
t 'til eleven o'clock. And then me dad give me a key. He said, you're twenty-one now, you can have a key. And I got so used to running me life, and I were courting, I used to leave me girl at about five to eleven and run back home for eleven o'clock. We l
ived on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 Chorley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 Old Road at time and they lived - didn't live so far and I never used that key, I were always in at eleven o'clock because simply I'd been brought up to it. And it hadn't wore off me, I didn't know - I knew I'd got key and I could use it but
 - I never had any inclination to use it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What age were you when you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well I should say - round about - six to seven when me dad used say - time go bed and soon as he said that we never said anything, we simply we
nt to bed and that was it. We was told to go to bed at nine o'clock, quarter nine and there was - we was away then. He didn't tell us twice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You got yourselves ready?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 We got ourselves ready. We were always had to go in kitchen and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 wash}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 hands}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 and your face before you went - that were one thing me mother made us do, for fear we were ever late at morning, going day school, we always had a wash at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 share}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  the bedroom with your brothers didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you share the bed with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Yes. There - there used to be - me other two brother and myself sleep in one bed. A full size bed. And me sisters slept in another one in another full size bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 It'd be a bit of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 squeeze}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  then wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well 
that's how - well all the beds at time was right agen the wall as there was only one could fall out. And sometimes you might sleep two at top and one at bottom but the bed were always set out for three at top. And then me brother started, me brother got }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and it lowered it down and lowered it down 'til it just left one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How often did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Every Monday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So you had your bath on Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And clean clothes on Monday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - Sunday like we always - Sunday - you had your best suit on, you had your clean clothes on but Monday, like when they started work, you always had your working clean overalls on, that's what I meant to say. Your clean clothes were always on, undercl
othes at Sunday. But your working clothes always at Monday; morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Where did you have your meals, you had the kitchen and the scullery downstairs didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Downstairs we had front room. We had - always our meals in kitchen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That was a sort of living kitchen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Same as here, like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was the sink in the scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 The sink was in scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Where was the cooking done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That was in't - house part - in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was it a cooking range, a fire range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Ordinary - ordinary fire range with your oven built onto your fire range. You did your cooking in your oven off your fire, old fashioned way, there were none of this having a gas cooker. We just had a little gas ring when we wanted boil our water 
for make a quick cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Which room did you actually have your meals in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there ever any occasions when you would eat anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, we always had our meals in't kitchen and - then the pots were took into - into - scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 About what time would you have breakfast? Remember that these questions are still related to your childhood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes, that's what I understand, that's what I mean. Well you could always say we'd had our breakfast at Sunday by nine o'cl
ock. During week you could say it was ready for about quarter past - half - eight o'clock to quarter past. We were starting getting ready for school then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 During the week who would be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Me mother. And me brother and me other sister. The others had gone out to work then, you see, they started six o'clock at morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did they manage for their first meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well me mother got up with 'em. Well they used to take their breakfast with 'em you see. They had - they started work at six o
'clock 'til eight. Then from eight o'clock to half past eight were breakfast time at the works and they'd have their sandwiches put up at night. Sometimes were put up at morning. Sometimes at night. So as when they got up they could have a cup of tea off 
gas ring and then get off to work. But mother always saw she was always up with 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did you usually have to eat and drink for your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - it was mostly - toast and porridge. Bar Sunday. And Sunday was your - glorious day when yo
ur father got it ready. Now that was - that was really a good breakfast, was Sunday, but your others might be porridge or it might be toast and jam or it might be jam butties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Drink of tea, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about the midday meal, what time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - they always used to come home for about - quarter past twelve. Works closed at twelve and they'd get home and you'd have tater pie, broth, lobschouse. We always had a cooked meal when we got home bar Friday. Now Fri
day, I can always remember it being a fish and chip day. Now at that time, you could go to chip shop and you could get a threeha'penny mix. That was chips, peas and a tail end of a fish. That was a fluke. And Friday afternoon it was baking day for me moth
er. She used do her own baking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Bread you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Yes, baking her bread and she hadn't time to make you a meal so we all, they had chips while it - because it were baking day and she'd have all her cleaning, then there were all fire irons wanted cl
eaning, well a lot of that was done at Thursday night, me sisters might help her, help me mother like and do all fire, punch and judy, lion and unicorn, home sweet home and all things what today people laugh at 'em. But in my time them was things what wan
ted cleaning and they wanted - they did want some cleaning. No honestly it's - it's true though that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You mentioned lobschouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Do you know what that word lobscouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I would like you to explain what it is if you would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well it's a
 tater pie without crust. That's put in - put in a pan, potatoes you cut your potatoes up, onion and pie meat, chopped. And it was just simply put on boiled on your gas ring and that was served up to you you see. It's just a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 tatie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  pie without a crust on. A
nd then you'd have rice pudding, we'd always have rice pudding, but it were a - it weren't these rice what you buy in tins, your mother - swelted it down herself in hot water. I can remember her doing that. That were her first job for - swab rice down, ma
ke it come up or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have rice pudding every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have a special dinner on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Oh yes, we always had a - we give it the works at Sunday. Because me father were at home and he see'd us 
- it were a real good do. At that time, I've gone in town for me mother at Sat'day morning and I've gone to stores at Wentworth Fish market used be and get a leg of mutton or leg of lamb and it were half a crown to three - to three shilling. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 Go from there 
to Leptons in - again market, for one and three pence you got two pound of sugar, quarten of tea and a piece of currant cake, about a pound of currant cake for one and threepence and then for going all them errands she used give me threeha'pence and I cou
ld go into Market Hall I could get ha'penny cup of wine from under clock and a penny boiled ham sandwich. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
That was in't market hall. Now that's going back a bit now you understand. But you're smiling there but - them is the real things what I used to do at Saturday morning as a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have a drink at dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Drink of tea. I've had ha'penny drink of wine. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 
It were a noted thing in my days to go into - into covered in market in which they sell the wine now at the same place under the clock
 and you used to get ha'penny drink and it was wine, it wasn't like intoxicating or anything like that, it was just blackcurrant wine what you wanted - and the same place you go in yet.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 At home when you had your dinner did you have a drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Always a drink of tea. Oh yes. We had tea breakfast, dinner and tea time. Probably at night we might have - or we might have cold water.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you were going to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When we were going at bed at - oftener than not if we wanted anything in were c
old water. I can't remember tea being made at night for us. Only for me - older brothers and sisters but for me it were cold water or else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about your meal at tea time, was that timed for when your father and brothers and sisters came home from work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - we were all at home. Now at them time round }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 our}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  street a fishman used come round, mussels, selling mussels and cockles you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 
Kippers, one man'd come round with a box of kippers on his shoulder and he'd be selling 'em all round, he wer
e a fishmonger but they used to come round, probably your mother'd buy some mussels or cockles, boil them for your father and me being youngest now I, me father always put me some on a plate. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Then me sisters'd probably have something else, I can't just tel
l you what they'd have, but they'd have finish up with jam pot. Jam pot'd be on table. You see. But I couldn't just tell you exactly what they was having, only - I can only remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You mean that your mother got the fish or whatever it was mainly for your father and you got it as a tit-bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
I did. Yes, me father always put me some at one side but me sisters and me brothers what were being older than me what was working they got - a plate of their own kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 But of the same fish or whatever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 It might be same fish. Yes, it would be same fish like but - they weren't big lovers of mussels and cockles then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So they had something different did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Probably finny haddock. What was - it was cheaper, or they m
ight have kippers, you see, well that'd be a Monday. And then she'd find something else for during the week. But we all had to sit down together. There was no one sitting down at one time, we all would wait - we always had to wait 'til - me father and we'
re all down together, there were no messing about that. He sat in rocking chair and when he said go you started. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have bread and jam as well as whatever else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. If you wanted bread and jam or - marmalade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well you only had to have home made cakes when your mother had made 'em. She - she - we had then - we had our home made cakes twice a week - Wednesday and Friday coming - and then them Friday, what was made at Friday was on for Sat'day and Sunday. A
nd there was any left it might go a bit longer, they might go a bit shorter depend if anybody come like, you brought any lads with you. Will you have a cake, well were less for you when you - they wouldn't last as long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You had a special do on Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. That
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 For tea as well as your other meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes, that was when she'd roasted a lamb and we all sat down and we had lamb and pickles, home made pickles like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your mother make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. No. She bought her own jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about bottling fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No she never bottled any fruit that I can remember of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was there ever any wind or medicine or beer made in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - it's only beer I can remember is me father. Now he always liked a pint every night.
 And he had it. Every night he had a pint of beer and half an ounce of bacca.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was this beer brought in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Brought in for him, oh yes, he never went out drinking it during week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 But you didn't do any home brewed beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no. No, no, no. We had our home made pop, we used make our own - home made ginger beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Who did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Me dad. And he made his own red cabbage and pickled his own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 shallots}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  for Christmas. We never bought any pickles, red cabbage and shallots was always made at ho
me by me dad. And you bought your own vinegar acid from chemist and gravy browning, you made your own vinegar because it were cheaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about medicines, did your mother or father make any herbal medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. No. The only thing is if we eve
r had a cold on top of fire place there were always black treacle and bacon, if you ever had a sore throat, I can remember at house, it was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 dollop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  of black - of fat bacon put round your neck and that used cure you. And your black treacle with bacon fat i
n it. And you just simply went and got it out of your pint pot and took a spoonful of it when you wanted it. That's only thing I can remember of having anything made at home, what did you any good. You're smiling again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 The way you said that if there was something else you had that didn't do you any good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well, I were big believer in home made old fashioned methods and - today I think if a lot of people'd take a little bit more black treacle, bacon fat and keep it warm on the top of your firepla
ce and take a spoonful I think you'd find out you wouldn't have as many sore throats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have any facilities where you could grow vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So you would buy all your vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, we never - our house was never had any - any gardens to it, and we never had allotment in me dad's time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you buy tinned, dried or fresh fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well me mother used to buy a lot of fresh fruit and - at them times you know there wasn't a lot of ti
nned fruit knocking round. You see, you're asking a question there when I were a little lad there weren't a lot of tinned fruit knocking around. You did your own like, you bought your own pears and boiled and cooked 'em for Sunday and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 About how often during the week would you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well you'd have meat - like pie meat and stewing steak and boiling beef, we nearly had meat every dinner time nearly, bar Friday. When Friday were cleaning day at home for me mother. We had boiling beef like
 that was, you know, it weren't expensive meat then, boiling meat and they made the broth off it for dinner time and you had it cold at tea time, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was there any tinned meat at all in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Cold meat. We had that for tea times many a time. In fact - sometimes you could - we've had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 potatoe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  pie made out of corned beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your parents keep any livestock for the family, hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from people poaching?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 It wouldn't be the right area for that would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well round Raikes Clough there were some round there but we hadn't - I can never ever remember any - coming in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you remember seeing your mother ever have less to eat so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - I can't remember it, but probably she would have done many a time, had a bit less, but I can't remember it, understand, but probably it might have happened as I haven't took notice that is a question what - I'll tel
l you, there were always a good thing about me father, now you're not taping it now are you? Oh yes, yes. Now me grandmother. Now me father were always one, every Friday night I used to go up to me grandmother's take her a shilling. That was off me father
 
to his mother you understand me and they used to give me, when I took it to me grandma, I used get a ha'penny for taking it, but he always saw as that shilling went to his mother 'cos me mother's mother were never in need of it, you see. Probably she'd ha
ve got same if - if she'd have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 needed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  it. But that were one thing as I always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 praised}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  me father for was always sending that - it was only a shilling but it were always welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your father have bigger portions of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I fancy he would d
o, yes, oh yes. Like many a time I can remember having top of thing and him having t'other. But you'll find out as your father's meals was always better than what you could get it ready yourself. Now the same thing happens today. I can be having egg and b
acon and me daughter can come home and I'll ask her will she have a sandwich and she'll - she'll tell you this present time as I can always flavour stuff better than what she can for her own palette. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your father take an active part in preparing food for you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - when we was having our meals like I was youngest, I'd off me father, he'd give me - I'd have a plate there and then me dad'd take it off - off his plate and put it on mine plate but me brothers and sisters'd have their
 own plates but what me dad give me it was on my plate, I always got a fair share bear in mind, but I wanted more I'd only need but I never had to need to ask. I would have got more if I'd have wanted 'cos he were a very strict chap and he believed in bei
ng strict with you and you had to obey him and - he looked after you well and you had to show appreciation by doing what you were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you allowed to talk at the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. That was one thing we wasn't. And at night, when they'd all come i
n, me father'd come home from work and he'd pick Bolton Evening News up while tea was being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 set}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 on the table then we'd all sit down, have our tea and then there was no talking. And then he'd come away from table and we came away then. Now}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407  if anybody}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  wanted
 pick that paper up they could pick that paper up while he had a smoke, you see, he had a pipe of bacca. Then when he finished that pipe of bacca that paper must be on the table for him ready to him starting reading. He had a matter of half an hour to gla
n
ce through paper at night time and then when he'd finished with it, when he was getting him ready, getting washed like for night you could all have a look at it. If you were in, 'cos you used like get out as quick as you could after you'd had your tea, be
cause if you stayed in and you started making any noise you were upstairs. So you got out as quick as you can.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407  no picking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and choosing when
 your mother put it on your plate. If you left anything you got in bother. You weren't supposed to leave anything 'cos what was good enough for them were good enough for you, and they ate it, you had to eat it.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What sort of bother would you get in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well you'd get shouted at like and you wouldn't get order - ordered away from table or anything like that but you'd be made to eat it, in fact I can remember time when me brother next to me, there was some fat meat on table, boiling meat and he wouldn
't eat it and he had to stop at that table 'til he did eat it and we'd all left the table and none of us had to go out 'til he ate it and he ate at finish, he never refused after, he always ate }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  was in front of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask for it or did you have to wait for it to be offered round?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no you'd ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You could have asked for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. If it were there you could ask for more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, you was t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 aught}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  how - I was taught at table as - I've never changed me ways. And I think I can go and eat with anybody at present day and that was how I taught at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Could you ever bring toys or a book to the table at mealtimes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh no. No, that were one thing you - the table was for eating off and that was its sole - and when you'd finished at table the pots were taken off straight away, washed up and the table was put back agai
n. Then you could play on the table with - and at that time there was engines like little lads had engines and that, you could play on table and - there were no white table clothes then. There was - a kind of a plastic you see, wash - like a wash leather 
thing you see and they washed it down but there was always this tablecloth on and it was clean and you ate off that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When could you leave the table, when your father had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Could you ask to leave before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When we'd ha
d - finished - had what we'd had - what we wanted you could say - you'd say to your dad, can I go out now dad? He may say - if he said yes, well you could go. If he said wait, well you had to wait. I couldn't get up away from table than - and get up on me
 own accord, I had to say to me father, can I go out now dad? He'd probably say yes, but if he didn't speak I had stop there 'til he said yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And it was always your father you had to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well, we always ask - it were always with me dad say, can
 I do this, dad, can I do that dad, very rare your mam, you know, you said to your mother, if your dad weren't in you'd say, well can I go out mam or something like that, but otherwise it were nearly your dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And it was your mother who served out was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Me mother what served it all out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What order did she serve you in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well it - well that's a question what I can hardly answer you that now in, you know, direct. But alwa
ys me dad plate was always there first and then it was - I think it went to anybody, tell you the truth. I couldn't say whether it were me - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 eldest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  sister or - but they all used get it but I can't tell you how they got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you were very young, before you were able to sit up to the table, do you know how you were fed then, did you have a high chair?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - I had an high chair, I can remember that. In fact - I remember it going to me oldest - to me oldest sister to their child - youngster and
 the time it had been; painted, time and time again, and it was one just with ordinary flung. It was straight one, there was no putting it in two like they have at present and you had to slide in and leaf come over top of you and I always at, it were alwa
ys put against me dad, in between me dad and me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 About how old would you be when you sat to the table properly, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - I should say about - three year old and I were put on a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 cushion}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  between me mother and dad, I still had
 me place there between me mother and me dad and me mother were always last to sit down because where she was serving out from you see she always used to be over on this side while she were serving it out to bring it onto the table, so me mother were alwa
ys last. But we all - always had to start together. That were one thing me dad always saw to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You speak as if you were a little bit closer to your father than your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You weren't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. If anything I were more closer to me mo
ther because I could get what I wanted off me mother. Very easy. But when - once me dad had given me his threeha'pence I'd had it now to soft heart come to him during week you'd go to him and say, can I have some toffee? He might give you one then but you
 
could nearly always assure your mother would buy you some toffee. In meantime if she had the money to do it you could always make sure she'd see you had a bit of toffee. Never lot bear in mind. But I were always well blessed with good aunties and good unc
les. And they lived in the same street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well me mother was deaf and - she was very - anybody could have got on with mother. Only a small woman but she'd heart like gold. She really had. She had really. She were a good - a good lady, she'd help anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 If you were worried about anything did you feel that you could talk to her easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh talk to me mother. Oh yes, yes. I'll give you an instance now when I started; working, I'm going a little bit
 far beyond the time and I got - took, me wage home, always took it home to me mother you see and I'd be a matter of twenty you see and I was serving me time as a mouler and I used get ten shillings spending money. That were a lot in them days and when me
 
mother died starting on me first weeks wage like as I come home I didn't know who to give it - me sister was living with us, I didn't know who to give it to, whether I give it to me dad or give it to me sister. Anyway I told me sister and she said, give i
t
 to your dad. And I can remember me dad saying to me, how much spending money did your mother give you? And I said, ten shilling. And I can remember him swearing over it. He says, well, if thee mother give thee then shilling I'll give you ten shilling and
 he vive me ten shillings. Now I'd no trouble with me mother, I could borrow off me mother and never pay it back, I'd offer it her at Friday but she would never take it. But offer it to me dad, he'd take it. Oh yes, he - he didn't believe in }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 borrowing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Your mother was more indulgent that your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you find you could talk to him about anything if you were worried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Yes. Even when I started working he asked me what I wanted be. Whether I wanted follow his lines in engi
neering works or go in moulding shop where me grandfathers were moulders and I said, well I'd - I'd like go in a moulding shop because some of me pals had gone in so I went in and he were a fellow like that, he he'd have a talk to you and ask you how you 
w
ere going on at work and he had plenty of his spies about you see, where he - when he worked at Hicks and I served me time there some of his mates used go at Saturday dinner time having a drink with me dad well then me dad'd start asking them how were I g
o
ing on. And if I weren't doing right I used get shouted at when he come home. As I were - he kept us - has his spies out kind of thing to look after us. Then me other brother were engineer turner and fitter, me oldest brother, at Hick and Hargreaves. Then
 
me next brother didn't take to it, he went working in a shop. Now I went in foundry you see and I enjoyed it. But - he had his spies out to see as we didn't - go beyond our line same as smoking, I one time caught me smoking and - me mother didn't bother. 
I
 were a matter of fifteen and it were on Choley Old Road and I was smoking and talking to me mother and me mother were talking to another woman and me dad looked at me, he said, get into th'house. Well I went in and threw me packet of Woodbines on fire th
i
nking now I'm going to get a good telling off. He never hit use Well he didn't no need to hit us with telling off he give us. And when he come back home from having a drink he'd forgot all about it and I'd thrown me cigarettes in. See what I - but me moth
er you could -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was he quick to be angry and then it blew over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh when he shouted at you he meant it for a - you didn't need a second telling. for a while after 'til you'd thought yourself you're getting a little bit too big and you just wanted c
opping down a little bit then he'd clap you down again. But he wouldn't - he'd never no need to hit us. He could get it home without hitting. Really he could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your mother ever punish you at all for anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I can't remember me mother ever - she were too - too soft hearted me mother was. Too soft hearted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards them in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, we always had to show respect to me - to me mother and father, even me oldest two sisters
. Like me other, me brother next to me and me sister I - I could please meself kind of thing if they wanted me go errand or anything I could please myself. But me other two oldest sisters - they asked me to do anything I did it about - 'cos I had to show 
respect to old people - to people older than myself. And I were brought up that way, and I still do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your parents say you should hit back or not if another child hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - they saw - they always told me had to stick up for myself. And if I were in a fight and - round where I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 lived}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 at time, in Nile Street, we mated in gangs and we had a fight and you went home worse well they used tell you get out and stand on your own two feet. That's all what we got. We'd never go out and - tackle 'e
m for you. He'd make you stand on your own feet as you know'd what you were doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I think myself they expected us all our family to grow up and respect them and old p
eople. That's what I - that was always their intention as I were always brought up and they always seemed to give me that, to respect old people and - do - do a good turn for anybody and - me father always, and me mother, always used tell us that. Help pe
ople and they'll help you when you want it and that's how I were brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they bring you up to think that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - they brought me up to make me understand as I had a responsibility in life to look after. I had to look after }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 myself}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 and I was somebody on this world, I wasn't just put there and I pleased myself, I had - I had to make something out of me life, it hadn't to be wasted, that's one idea as I got off me parents. And off me sisters and me brother
s that were idea I got off them. To not to be satisfied in one place to grow and make life worth living for yourself and see how far you could get to top of tree. And in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13960796\charrsid14966407 today's}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  life that's what is the idea. You can - you can get a class of people what'll 
get in one groove and they're satisfied. You understand me, to stop there and they don't care whether they rise or they sink, they're not particular, they're just there and no - nothing else bothers. But I always that inclined to - work as hard as you can
 and it'll get you somewhere. In which it has done for me. I'm quite satisfied with what's gone on how me - how my family's come out. I've no regrets of anything I've done. I'm }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 very}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 pleased}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  with my life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When grown ups were talking when you were a child were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 At home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 At home or in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Ah well you see, I served me time in a foundry. Now in a foundry, a lad - lads sit with lads, men sit with men, you understand. Now you never got in conversation with them,
 you were a lad and you had to stop a lad. Now when you come twenty-one and you come out of your time you went sitting with men, you left the lads, you see, you were a man then but you didn't speak when you went sitting with men. Not 'til you were a matte
r of about twenty-two or twenty-three 'til you sta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
ted voicing your opinion to 'em. You weren't allowed speak, you were just there. They were men, we were just coming up to men and you drifted with the lads at one side, you didn't bother with 'em, 'cos you 
coming that stage as manhood and in a foundry there were no talking back to men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about at home, could you join in a conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Join in with me sisters, debate on anything, we've had many a good night debating things, you know. Sa
y, all what - what you've done and one thing and another. Then me father, when we'd all got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
, he always believed in us all going home at Sunday. See me father lived with me sister so we all went home at Sunday like I went home, me wife and me childr
en, me brother and his two lads and his wife, then me other sisters lived - out of town so they didn't come but we always used to come home at Sunday night to me dad you see and - play cards, make your own won entertainment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you were quite a small child and your mother and father were talking could you join in the conversation then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, you were told shut up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 If your mother was talking to a neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I always - I were always told shut up. When me mother were talking to an
ybody I could - I could start when there were nobody else speaking and I mustn't get on same subject, if I was - I couldn't say to her well, you're wrong or she's wrong. I should be told to shut up and mind me own business. No messing about with that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can you remember any particular occasion when your father punished you, how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - I can remember one time in particular. It was pancake Tuesday, you see. Now all apprentices used to have to go - go out of foundry at e
leven o'clock, they didn't work you see. You had to go home, you had a half a day off Pancake Tuesday. And I'd gone out with all t'other lads you see, came home dinner time, and me dad was working at same engineering place, Hick and Hargreaves, he; says, 
what's do? He knew what were do but he wouldn't tell me, he were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 awaiting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 my answers. Oh, I said, we have to have half a day off, we have no pig iron, you see. So he said, all right, you know, never bothered. So when he come home at night, he came home from
 work, I came home, have you enjoyed yourself? I said, yes. He said, did you say you had no pig iron? I said, well that's what they told me. And we all had go out, I says, a fellow called Frank Critchley told us we all had to go out, he told this lad for 
l
ot of us you see. Well, he says, you had pig iron, why did you tell me a lie? You see, I'd told him a lie. So he chastised me over it. So he wouldn't let me go work at morning after. I had to stay in. And I stayed in from Tuesday to Friday. I daren't have
 
gone out of our house fearing him coming home during daytime and catching me out. He told me I'd to stop in. And I had to stop in and I did do and then I had go work first thing Friday morning when he told me I could go work. But he made it right with for
eman what I were - what I got for going home telling him fibs kind of thing and I - I really got it. And that were punishment was staying in and when he come in I weren't - nobody spoke to me kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I felt 
terrible. Really. And I think that was one lesson as I always remember and I think it brought me to me senses, you understand me. As - it brought me as - why should I gone home when I know'd what I were doing and not having the sense enough to go and tell
 
me father and he worked at same place as we were short of pig iron, you see, it proved it to me as I were a fool, it got me nothing only got me a good shouting at and some fathers'd have give 'em a good hiding but I didn't get one, my punishment were I ha
d to stay in. And I think that pulled me up more quicker than anything. I honestly think that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did your parents think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh they didn't swear a lot. No. Oh no. No. We'd - very rare hear me dad - if he swore he were bad tempered.
 Something had got right onto him and - then he'd give it you and when he did - everybody had - get out of road, get upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one of them play a more impor
tant part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - me father were more stricter. But the - than me mother but me mother were always one what - she'd shout at you, understand me, and she'd make you cry without hitting you and she'd soon then after she - when she see te
ars coming she'd mar you. Then me dad wouldn't. Now soon as me dad knew as you were cracking up - he'd send you to bed, and you stayed there. But come in at night before you had to go to sleep he'd shout at you for come down and then he'd say, now you und
erstand what you've been sent bed for? And then it'd be finished. He'd carry no malice after. No, he never carried any malice. He'd give it you with his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 tongue}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and he could rap it home at you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, yes. Yes, you always got a present on your birthday. Oh yes, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Just one present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well, you'd get one off your father and mother and probably your sisters and brothers'd club together and buy you - something. But - you're 
not reckoning your aunties and your uncles like, just - just in our own family - your mother and father'd give you something and your sisters and brothers'd club together and give you something. And that was your - same as like when fairground was on - th
e
y might - you might get a shilling off your father and sixpence off your mother and probably your sisters and brothers'd give you a copper or two. You could go and spend a good time up fairground with it. Same as at Good Friday, you'd be up at; six o'cloc
k
 of morning with - your sandwiches, hot cross buns and sandwiches and your cup and you go to Barrow Bridge. Come back again you'd have had - spent about a shilling, your mother and father'd say, oh you've got that shilling, probably your sisters might hav
e give you a ha'penny or penny. But you had good outings and they were, they were good as you could - have a good outing at Barrow Bridge. Rivington Pike, been up there many a time Good Fridays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have any special festivity when it was your birthday, a party - anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh no, you wouldn't - we wouldn't have anything - your mother would make a cake probably or a - apple pie or a jam pie and - like you'd make your table'd be set out a little bit better than ordinary days but it
 only happened mostly to me that like because t'others had - their birthdays didn't matter as much as what it did with me like being youngest of family and they'd say, well - this is your birthday party and probably you'd have a - apple pie or a jam pie o
n table and a home made cake you see. Probably jelly. But - they - they just say that were your birthday you took it for granted it was your birthday party you see. But you never invited anybody in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can you remember how you used to spend your Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Christmas Day? When I were a youngster? I can. Really good. Really good Christmas, I always used to hang me stocking up. And our }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 John}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 , that's me brother next to me, and our Sally, me other sister, and we always hang them on me dad's, we always 
got apples and oranges, nuts, toffee and presents. Yes, I remember that and it were a day as - you could always remember because your father and mother, you'd have a good breakfast, thee'd have probably chicken or - anything like that, you know, jelly, pl
enty of jelly and plenty cakes, oh yes, they were glorious times Christmas time. glorious time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you go out or spend the day at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh spend our - at home. Always at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you go to church as a family on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. Me
 father wasn't one - to go to church a lot but he believed in the family going. We had to go kind of thing. He were a fellow like this, it's not what I do, it's what I want you to do, you see. Well in my life it's not been what I want to do to my children
, it's I've gone with 'em, they come with us where it were t'other way about at our house when I were a - a lad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So you spent your Christmas Day at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 At home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You didn't go to church or have friends or relations in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 We went Coe Str
eet Mission - at Sunday morning. Mission were open at Sunday morning, they you finished. You see, we never went church, it were Coe Street Mission as we did a lot at, you see, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You went there Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes, Sunday and then we'd finished. Yes. Showing our toys off more than anything That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have any musical instruments in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 We had a piano. Oh yes, we had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Who played the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Me sister could play it but she never had any lessons, it were just - what she could pick up herself but - oh and we'd a }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  too. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did anybody sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, we'd all join in you know like some of the - th'old favourites kind of thing. Same as they do at - at present time now at our h
ouse. Last Christmas we had twenty at our house, me family, friends, me sister and her daughter and we all went in front and we were all singing and playing games and that's - we spend our Christmas times like that and we still do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have sing-songs as a family at other times as well as at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Perhaps Sunday evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh Sundays we used play - play cards like. Me oldest sisters and brothers used play and then it got to time as they couldn't - they were to
o big, they wanted to go out or something like so it left it - me by meself you see. Well me dad never played cards with us. And me mother never played cards. So I could sit in and read or - have out - go out, as long as you were back for - soon enough fo
r when he wanted you. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. We always had books in th'house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 A lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - ordinary, you know, like - Chatterbox, some of them books like, you got 'em at Christmas time and - Chatterbox - ee
h, I couldn't tell you but there was - children's books. I always - we - they were always bringing children's books in and Comic Cuts, you see, you could buy Comic Cuts then for a ha'penny. After you'd read it you swap it with some of your school pals.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And you had the Bolton evening News?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have any other newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Just Bolton Evening News that were all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You say your father used to read it - what about your mother, did your mother or father read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can you remember there being a funeral in the family when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can I remember being a funeral? I were - grown up well then. I was grown up well it were me sister.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You can't remember one when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When I was small, no, not in our family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you taken out to visit your neighbours, friends and relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Yes. Taken out to me aunties and me uncles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was it your mother or father or both of them that took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh p
robably - me mother and me dad'd - go out with us. And say Friday - Saturday night me mother and - and me dad and me aunt and me'd go to pictures at Saturday night, or go for a tram ride, there were trams running in them days like, go on trams to - Horwic
h or somewhere like that, Daffcocker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. No. Only when I were going for anything new. I was took with me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you remember any outings with your parents - you told me about Good Friday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, I can remember outings. Now this is instance what you don't see today. I can remember in Nile Street a man had got a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 charabanc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
. Now you know what a charabanc is, is horses, two horses and a landau and they took us up to Four Lane Ends. There was women and the c
hildren, you see, and we walk, it was a Saturday afternoon outing and it was at Four Lane Ends that and we had our tea at Four Lane Ends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You took your tea with you did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Took our tea with us and then we got cups of tea in the pub when - when
 t'horses were being watered and fed. And then I can remember going for a whole day at Saturday. All day Saturday. That's Saturday morning - all day - that was Saturday morning to Saturday evening and we went to Atherton. That was just past Atherton Centr
a
l, the pub there and we had our tea in there. We'd stayed at Four Lane Ends for our dinner then from there we went to Atherton an matter of five mile - four mile and we stayed there and then we started coming back. That was with me mother and some friends
 in street. You see. Now their - their husbands didn't go with 'em, it was just mothers and children, I can remember that quite -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I think me first holiday I'd be a matter of eleven and I went with me sisters, m
e three sisters and we went to Isle of Man for a week. And I would be about eleven. I can remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you go regularly after that or was this just an isolated instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That was about me first holiday I had for a matter of ten year. 'Til I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 , 'til we started having our holidays. And then we had 'em regular then when I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you enjoy your holiday in the Isle of Man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, I can remember it quite plain. And an Aunt went with us. And me sisters had gone dan
cing and a youngster were with 'em what I were her uncle, one of me sister's girl and me aunt took us on sands at Saturday night, all along front, oh I enjoyed it really. I can remember putting me name in visiting book at Isle - in Douglas, quite well. I 
remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What sort of a place was it you stayed at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Just ordinary boarding house but I can remember it really - as I had a really jolly good time you know and I can remember putting me name in that visiting book and I thought I was somebody and
 we went on Viking - th'old Viking. And that was time when it was eighteen shilling to go to Isle of Man. That was from Bolton to Douglas. Steerage on boat. Yes, I remember that quite plain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you enjoy the journey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. In fact ever since we've been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  I think we've been to Isle of Man every year. 'Cos I had a sister lived in Isle of Man. You see. Then when I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and we had youngsters we couldn't afford holiday because trade was bad, you understand, so me sister was very good as w
e got saved up for our railway fare and that we went in a big hotel in Isle of Man and we took our family with us and we got A.1. treatment you see. And now - them times it were eighteen shilling to go to Isle of Man. And the - when we went first time I h
ad twenty-five shilling in me pocket, spending money and me wife had fifteen and she had two photographs in a little Brownie number two and it was - to have a new film and have the film developed was half a crown then. And we stayed at hotel and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can you tell me how you used to spend your Saturdays as a child, you've spoken about going for tram rides and going to the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Well you could go to temperance hall in Bridge Street and used to be a penny at Saturday afternoons and you got a st
ick of rock, that was Saturday afternoons. And then you just played about at Saturday night like after and there were these comics and cowboys, there were all that at Saturday and then at - say at Saturday night you'd go with a gang of lads and you'd play
 around - round t'houses, round corner, what they call corner you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about Saturday mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well Saturday mornings you used have go errands for your mother. Then there were an old lady called old Mrs McLennan and I used go her errands -
 I got a penny for going her errands. And it was - you were up to dinner time doing your mother's and doing your own - errands for this Mrs MacLennon. As I told you before you could have gone in town for - one and - one and six - one and threepence to get
 - currant cake, sugar, tea and sugar, I've told you all about that, and - well that were it, your Saturday mornings you'd enough to do at Saturday mornings doing - running errands for your mother and this Mr McLennan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Sunday.
 Well I had to go Sunday school Sunday morning. We got up - all got up, we'd all been bathed at Saturday night. Tin at front of fire like, there were no bathrooms, we hadn't a bathroom, and - Sunday school half past nine Sunday morning. Sunday afternoon S
unday school, take me clothes off when I come back after Sunday school at afternoon and put me - clothes what I wore for week on so as they could I could keep 'm a bit long while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You said your father wasn't in the habit of going to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Church. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well it were a mission and me mother used go say about - say twice a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was this the Coe Street Mission that you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Coe Street Mission, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you go to that mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was it their Sunday school that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 It was Sunday school as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you remember there being any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 
Yes, we used to have field days, what they call fields days then and it was a penny, yo
u took your own cup and you went on Manchester Road along Green Lane, there was a big field there and when you had you marched there and you had coffee and buns and played games, racing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Then at night there were a - Balliwell band came on and there were pe
ople dancing, everybody were invited. It were a great day then going for your fields days. At mission. That was once a year when we had the field days but the different classes had picnics like, we've gone to Barrow Bridge and I think Rivington Pike were 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 farthest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  we ever went to when - up to I started working like, with Sunday school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there any other social activities organised by the mission that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, they had a Boys Brigade, Church Lads Brigade, it was in - I were in Scouts. I were in First Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was that attached to the Mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
No. No, this was just ordinary - it had nothing do with church or anything like that, it was just - it were called First Bolton and - it were a troop in Bolton and I joined them a
s a Scout. I remember one time, we walked to Preston when war was starting, all Bolton Scouts of all Bolton and we walked to Preston and Davis, squeezers - squeezer maker from Nile Street, he was Septon for overall Bolton for Scouts and he went with 'em a
n
d when we got to Preston we slept in a joiners shop all night. Then we walked it back from Preston to Bolton at Sunday. It were eight o'clock when we got home, then when I got home I dropped on floor and I were asleep 'til Monday afternoon, 'cos I'd not -
 not been sleep'd at night you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was this a special endurance test?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
It were endurance test, we were supposed to get in all our lads as we could take care of ourselves. In fact we went on Belmont on reservoirs on Saturday nights some of us, gua
rd - supposed be guarding reservoirs for the - any Germans come over and we'd only our sticks with us. So - I did a bit of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - I was in St Barnabas choir, that's up Chorley Old Road, you see, we were living up there, and I was in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you going there at the same time as you were going to this Coe Street Mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, we'd left Coe Street Mission then, you see, and - because we'd gone living up Chorley Old Road. And I went to Gaskell Street scho
ol, finishing up like and I joined choir at St Barnabas. Well it were just ordinary mission hall and then we had a church built, I just - I can't just tell you year and I were a choir boy there and - Vicar were called Reverend Hayes. He were an old chap, 
a
 cripple. But he used take us out after choir at Sunday night, walks round Captains Clough and at top of Ivy Road and give us a apple. We helped him with christenings like taking water to font Sunday afternoons. Well I think I were in choir 'til I were ab
out sixteen there and then - got with a gang of lads and - we got falling off Sunday school 'til - I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did either of the churches have a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they have any other sort of organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well there was nothing, only Boys Brigade at - at Holy Trinity and at St Barnabas we had nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you go to Holy Trinity in between as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Now and again I used to go you know but - me church was then was St Barnabas but sometimes I'd go to - mission you see
 at Sunday afternoon but it wasn't me place that I were going to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was it the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 habit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  in your family for grace to be said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, we never did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I was always told by me mother and me d
ad to kneel at side of bed but it was like anything else, they never liked forced it, she used to say to you, have you said your prayers? And - they never come and watched us. Many a time we must admit we slipped up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you ever have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 family prayers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Now we come onto your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - at that time there was only as I can remember was - Liberals and Conservatives. Now me father were a real Liberal and I can remember him -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you know why he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Wel
l it probably his views were that way but - in them times it was, if your father were a Liberal you were a Liberal, if your father were a Tory you were a Tory. You didn't seem to take any interest in politics, you see, at the time and - I can remember whe
n
 they were starting - and it were voting for women and that. Me mother had a vote and we lived at Chorley Old Road and he said to her he said, now I want you go - come with me and vote. So she went to Oxford Road school voting, and he said, if you vote yo
u
'll get two glasses of brandy at Liberal club after. So he took her up voting and - me mother were deaf and - he bought her this brandy but when she were going in voting she - he were going in with her into stall like and a bobby what were there called ol
d
 Bobby Brookes, know me father very well, lived round there and he said, nay, he said, Jack, thou can't go and show her, he said, she'll only have put what I tell her. And then they went having their brandy. And she drank her brandy and - she never used g
o
 out like that only for a special occasion. And then she said to me dad, she always called him John, his name was John you see, oh John, can I have t'other brandy now? And - that were an experience as what me mother had with this night when she first went
 voting with me dad you see. And she - but she got her two bra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 dies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would she vote Liberal do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 She'd do what me dad told her. Me dad were number one at our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 In some places in those days people felt that they risked losing t
heir job or if they were in a rented house, losing their house if they voted differently from the way their employer wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh well we never - yes, well we never were in a house where you was fixed by employer. And me dad just - he were a Liberal an
d nobody'd have changed him, he were a Liberal like even 'til he finished. Well they come along as I come with - learning a little bit of life and I changed me policy. He never said anything to me and then when I got a vote I speak to me dad about it and 
he put his views but he thought I should have been a Liberal but I didn't turn out be one you see. I just used me own idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did you become?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 Labour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  man, I could only see that bringing us something in at the time. That was - reason that I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your father actually belong to the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
No, he - he only just belonged to Liberal club, you see, it were like Conservative club and Liberal club and - men could go and have a game of dominoes and - it was a cl
ub at night and he used go in at Saturday night for about - an hour or two hours and then he'd go in at Friday night for about an hour. You see, Saturday night after he took me auntie and me mother to pictures to Gem pictures first house, there used to be
 two houses then you see, and he brought 'em home, then he used to go into club himself then 'til ten o'clock after he'd brought 'em out from pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever take them with him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. No. Not at Saturday night. You see, it was a - at that time it were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 club, there were no women going in like at the present time. It were a - all men. Now it's changed from - in present time now they can take anybody in. At the time it were a one man - it were a club for men only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they never allow women in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well only probably at Christmas times when they were having Christmas parties, that was all that - at the time as I can remember it was just a working man's club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your father ever actually do anything at election time to help the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Only his trade union. He was - on committee at the trades union but - he never did anything, only just went to meetings and - he were shop steward for
 a while, I remember him being shop steward like that's collecting club money at Monday nights you see and taking it down for 'em. 'S' only thing but he would never - did anything really interesting in it, it was just - he were picked to be shop steward a
nd he was a shop steward. If anything went wrong at foundry well he'd have to go and see boss over it, for to see if he could get it right without starting a strike or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you remember a time when he did take part in such a thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. I can't remember him - when me father took any strikes - in any strikes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I mean, him taking a part in negotiation for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. No. Because he kept his own business to himself. What was his business outside, of his works or anything 
like that, that was his private business and it was nothing to do with us. So reason we never got know anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 He would never discuss anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, not in his - at home, what went on at foundry. It were foundry. When he got 
home it were all left where it should be left, at foundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
When your mother and father weren't actually doing their work did they spend their spare time in doing anything else other than what you've already }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 mentioned?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, I can't remember - reme
mber doing anything different than what I've already told you. Only I remember one time at Christmas time we lived in Chorley Old Road and we said we'd have our own hens at Christmas and we - we bought - me dad bought two cocks and we fed 'em up for Chris
tmas and New Year and I remember I looked after 'em. That's only thing as I can know they every did only it were - it were happy life and - everybody were comfortable at home, like me sisters but me oldest sister got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and then - me next sister got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
, then me brother went to work in down Portsmouth so as it left just - there was two brothers another brother and myself and me sister. And it were - me dad were boss, there were no two ways about that, and we didn't quarrel, it were happy home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, only going to mothers union. That was at - at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 Luke\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  you see, when we were living up Chorley Old Road she used go mothers union once a week and that were at Wednesday afternoon. That was - j
ust going and having cups of tea and a - a bit of a chat you know. Belonging to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 Luke\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did she become affiliated to that church then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, you see, well she used go there, like say about - say twice a month. Sometimes she'd - she w
ouldn't go for month and then probably she'd go about three times on the stretch. Just depend what was happening at Sunday if you'd had anybody, me brother are me sister brought anybody for tea and she were doing a little bit more well it got put at one s
ide, you got to wait to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did she go out to enjoy herself other than going to the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
No. That was one thing she never did only go to pictures with me dad. And at Thursday after - Thursday afternoon, if I were off school they used go up p
icture place in town where Timothy Whites is now and you could go there afternoon and you'd get a cup of tea and a biscuit, that was given in I think it was sixpence. Electric Theatre it were called, that was sixpence to go to there and I've been with her
 there at Thursday afternoons and you got your cup of tea and a biscuit and you watched pictures, that was sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 About what time would your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Round about half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Every - every evening bar Friday and Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did he ever attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Or bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you remember whether your mother or father belonged to any savings clubs, for sickness or funeral or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes, they was in - sick clubs you know, like - for what they put children in when they was born and that. Insurance, that was all. And he were a member of th' Oddfellows like. He
 were Oddfellow. But that's all, he were ever members of. 'Cos at them times you know - like before it come National Health, you had your own doctor you see, now we used to have a doctor called Doctor Patchet. And you didn't pay when you got your medicine
. You paid probably a shilling a week and doctor's man used to come round every Friday night and you'd pay your shilling, you see. That was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bull Lane{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} where that doctor lived, that were th'only doctor }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 we ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  had. Bull Lane, that was at Great Lever, you s
ee, well we were family doctor down there at Nile Street well he kept into family all time 'til he give over, doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You say it was a happy family and never any quarrels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. It was a really - and I'm not kidding you when I tell you - a real ha
ppy - when you were at home you were at home you enjoyed it and we didn't have a lot of fancy stuff but what we had was good, you understand. And at the time I can remember a butchers shop on Chorley Old Road where at Sunday morning you could take a jug a
n
d you could get threepenny worth of stew off him in a big jug. I can remember going for that for - for 'em. You see, it were what he'd ad left and he'd stewed it all up, it was stewed in ordinary boiler with a fire to, no special appliances like, and you'
d go and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 threepennyworth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and take your jug and it were threepence. I can remember that quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you feel that there was any one of your brothers or sisters that you were specially close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - I had a sister, me oldest sister, she were
 - really smart you understand, and - if you wanted any advice you went to her like, you know, because she - she seemed more capable than what me other brothers and sisters did. Well me two oldest sister was very smart indeed, in fact, they did well for t
heirselves you see and they always looked after home when they'd got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
, they always used to look after home, come and see me mother, me dad and - because they lived in Manchester at time they did. So it were really good - you know, you enjoyed it, you
 could take a friend home and - you could take 'em on Sat'day and you could have your Sat'days tea and you'd no say, well can I bring somebody home for a tea? You just took him home and he was treated as one of you. There was no asking could you do, you d
id do. That's where I say - where - it were home what you - you can rely on it, you was - well looked after and who you took home it were all right to me mother and me dad, and they could always get a meal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 As a small child who did you play with, would it be your bothers and sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well me brother next to me, what was just older than me, I used go with him like a lot and - then play with lads at - but if we were ever going anywhere, say Good Fridays and that, I always used go with
 me oldest - me - next me brother to me, that were our John and he always supposed had to looked after me like, see that I got back home all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you were playing for a short time round about home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you play in your own yard or in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Play in 't' street. In 't' back street - in 't' front street or at - bottom of Nile Street there was spare ground down there you see and you played on there a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you ever go into the other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  homes to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes, yes. One of my friends today now I - I speak a lot to him, we were really good pals, a lad called Jimmy Walsh and I can remember him falling over a wall and breaking his arm and when we took him home with a broken arm he got a good hiding off his 
mother for breaking his arm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 This was before he got any attention to his arm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Before he got - he was took to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 infirmary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 , there was ma and another lad took him home, and he got a good welting across face for going on 't' wall kind of thing, be
cause we shouldn't have been on it and he got welted for it. I remember that quite plain, in fact, we speak about it at - now, different times when I meet him in town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I don't think you'd understand them you
 see. Like we used play maps, slap round can, you understand what that - that's a can an a piece of string and you fellow hitting it and he were turning it round and you had to belt it with a stick, you see, but you hit stick and then you had to go and st
a
nd in middle. And - football. All sorts of - drop latch, that's going round with your cap and knocking on latch and then running off. Oh - oh we were - we knew all tricks. Then there was another trick what we used to play is getting a pin and a bobbin of 
thread and a button and putting it on the window and going and sitting over at t'other side and keep touching window. There were all that you know. Then I did a lot of swimming, I used go - we used go baths.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you allowed to get dirty when you were out playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh well - naturally you would get dirty. But if you got too much you got shouted at when you got in. Well it's - condition you went in but - you never bothered about dirt you know. And - I can remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 They didn't prevent you from doing the same sort of things again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh no, no, like if you went home very dirty and mother'd shout at you then she'd, get yourself washed before you come, you know, and you'd be in kitchen, whether it were cold or whether it weren't you'd stop the
re - til you got washed and then you'd go in. But you'd do it again. You see. You'd do the thing again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you free to play with anybody you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there any children at all that you were discouraged from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well there was - some older like you'd be in - in Nile Street, not Chorley Old Road, there were boys and girls, we used play together kind of thing you know. Like - jumping on back, what they call, putting a cap on your back and jumping on - jumping on
 back, putting your finger up saying how many. But we all played happily together? Now I come to think, we had more games then and enjoyed ourselves better than they do today. Oh. Hundred percent better - when I were a lad. And enjoyment I got than what t
h
e present people have today. And I think I can tell you th'reason. In me own mind. Today - these lads if they go an errand, give 'em threepence they look at you, but you'd run a mile, a couple of mile for a ha'penny. And you enjoyed spending that ha'penny
. But today now they don't enjoy it if they don't spend about half a crown. That's what I think myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have any particular hobbies while you were still at school, keeping pets or collecting anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well we always had a dog, we always had a dog. That was th'only hobby I - I had - we always had dogs, me father always had a dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was it his dog?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well it was t'house dog. It were me dad's dog but it were always with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you collect anything or do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no. Just play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you ever go fishing or cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh I had a bike and I did - but never any big distances and we used to go fishing on canal. That's down Manchester Road down there, well you see you had to have a fishing rights for there. Well 
when you went with the lads we didn't have any rods we just had a bit of cane what you can buy ha'penny cane, get some thread and go fishing and - soon as bank man were coming along you were off. With you tin, you only fished with worms, you didn't have a
ny special stuff or anything like that like they have at present. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 But you used to go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes. Yes. You had to entertain yourself more with - going out, going up to - like round Townleys up to - up - up top of Great Lever. Plenty pla
ying fields round there. Go on Manchester Road, you'd plenty playing fields. Oh you'd - more playing facilities than what there is today. 'Cos it were more open you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 By playing fields you just mean fields don't you? Not set out as playing fields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh no, just a gang of you set out and - take a ball with you, play football, or - anything in for any trouble being knocked about - being a little, say a little rascal, you were in it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you take part in any sports other than walking and swimming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I didn't - I played football for Chorley Old Road }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 Gang}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  like later on in life that were all that - I were never a good'un.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you ever go to a theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. I've been to Grand in gods, that used to be threepence in the
re with gang of lads at Friday night and then come out of there, you'd two houses there, well I were one always had to go first house because had to be in soon. And then we'd go to pie shop. Tha's over Karl Walsh's. And they used to be a penny for a pasty
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - I've been Sunday school concerts. That were about all. Only Sunday school concerts.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Not concerts in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh Grand were a music hall. Grand at Bolton. Must be pulled 
down now. And I've been to theatre and there was Hippodrome. I've been there at - Friday nights with gang of lads you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was it the music hall you went to rather than see a play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, it were mostly - it was only theatre what was for plays
. And Grand and Hippodrome was turns on you see. Oh I've been - been to them a time or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You've told me about the pocket money you got from your mother and father and the ha'pennies from your brothers and sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did you spend your pocket money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well it were mostly on toffee. Mostly on toffee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you save any of it for special occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - I were very fortunate that way, if there were anything special on as I want like, go anywhere, they'd have a -
 they'd all club together, me sisters and me brothers and make me about nine - sixpence to ninepence and then I were a bit short well I depended on me mother. And then me dad'd put - but save up I were - I never did save up a lot because I could always de
pend on me family, me sisters and me brothers giving me something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You mentioned there was the woman to help your mother with the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Mrs Leptrot that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
No, only just - only just me mother and me sisters and me two of me oldest sisters didn't do a lot it were depended on the youngest sister like. She were older than me, understand. But she used to have to help like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about friends or neighbours, did they help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Oh yes. There was - neighbour'd come in if you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 ever sick.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  I mean to say, anybody were ever ill they'd come in and help, do something for you and go your errands or help you do a bit of cleaning. Oh yes, we - they were good neighbours.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 If your mother was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
You could always rely on a neighbour coming in and getting your meal ready if you hadn't got it ready yourself. Or bring you a meal in, you see, cook it at their own home and bring it in for you. You could always rely on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did the relatives who lived nearby do this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - they lived far away you see. Had only two aunts what lived in - I'm speaking now in Nile Street you see and - one were a teacher and me other aunt w
as a - a weaver and - they hadn't - never enough time you see. But if we ever wanted anything, say - me and me other brother, we'd always go to me aunts. Say wanted any string or anything like that and you hadn't got it at home you could always go there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How much did your parents see of these aunts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh well, they'd come round - not a lot you know but if anything were wrong or anything like that you'd always depend they'd be there you understand. Like an uncle what kept - th'Oddfellows Arms}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14966407  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 - up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 Dubhill}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
, now you go up there like if you wanted anything, you'd go up there and it were me mother's sister you see and go up there you'd have sometimes you'd go for your tea. Then sometimes they might come to your house. But it wasn't often you see, I mean 
like they - they didn't make it occasion, probably me aunt'd come by herself. Same as probably me uncle Tom'd come by himself but they very rarely come in families you see like bringing their own children with 'em. They'd come separate kind of thing. And 
we used to go up to there. But my dad were a fellow what - never went out a lot to parties or eating out a lot. He always believed having his meals at home. I don't - I can't remember me dad ever going away for a weeks holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have friends visiting as well as relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes. We had friends of me mother's and father's and then there were friends of me sisters would come you know and - say during week and stopping and all have a bit of a sing-song in t'house but - they - me dad never wer
e a big - goer out like going to places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your mother and father have the same friends or did your mother have her own and your father have his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - well you see in them - your dad would say at Friday night, I'll go and have a drink, S
aturday night - well they would be his friends. Now me mother had just have her neighbours you see what - what were neighbours in 't' street which were one what me mother were and she always - told us not to go in a lot of people's houses making, you know
, sitting there all night. Now she were never one like that my mother. Her home, she would she'd be at our - anybody wanted her you'd always find her at home, she never used gossiping shall we say that like you see a - a lot of 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would you say then that people who came to the house would be actually invited to come rather than coming casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh they'd come in casually, they wouldn't be invited.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about you going in other people's houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - always stopped without I went in 
with some of me pals where I were palling with and they say I come into our house, naturally you'd go in then. You'd go and shout of 'em and if he ask you in you'd go in. But you wouldn't be in for long you know because you'd have to get out and get playi
ng.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would your mother go into other people's houses? Would she call in casually or would she have to be specially invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Now that were one - that were one thing me mother never did do a lot of gossiping, now I call it gossiping. She never went 
in a lot of people's houses, never. And - my family's been brought up same, now I'm coming up to present time. Now my wife never goes in - I don't think she's been in three houses in this street for this last seven year because she doesn't like gossiping.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 But would your mother accept an invitation to go into somebody's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, yes. See anybody, now say now - anybody what were ill. Now they wouldn't have to ask me mother, oh Mrs So and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 So's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  ill. No sooner me mother knew she'd go in and she'
d knock at door, can I do anything for you? Can I mop your flags? Can I do a bit of baking for you? Anything like that? Do a bit of cleaning. Take her - say some beef tea in a morning if she were really ill. Oh she were all a woman like that and - she wou
ldn't want asking if there were any sickness about, we put it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Friends did call in casually without an invitation didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would neighbours call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - probably might do, you know, t
hey were passing by and they say they looked through 't' window them time they were lace curtains you know and you could see anybody and they'd come round saying Mrs So and so and Mrs so and so like. But - they wouldn't be asked to come in, they'd knock a
t door and then, well you'd have to - she wouldn't stand on 't' doorstep talking to people, me mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would people who dropped in be offered something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh - they wouldn't - only they were coming in like - the arrangements had be
en made as they was coming in for a meal but they wouldn't be in - asked to come in and have a cup of tea and do a bit of chatting with me mother, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You mentioned this business about making their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 This applied to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When your parents got together with their friends was it largely a question of having a sing-song?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there other activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, it'd be more - talking. I don't think - my father and mother 
was them people what could - make - a lot of friends and going out and having - like going out - going to houses and having a sing-song. It'd just be having a - something to eat and talking. They wasn't - and playing any games - they wasn't particular any
t
hing like that. Or playing cards. Like me father and mother could never play cards. They'd just sit talking, they were never good - make any promise at singing, only - when we were by ourselves at family then me dad, he'd have a drink or two he'd sing som
e of his old songs. You know, and - well we've learned 'em and we carry on with same old songs. Same old songs as what were sung when I were a lad at Christmas times and that. They're being sung at our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 People often divide society into different 
social classes, in the time prior to 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one social class and others to a different one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Yes. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can you tell me something about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - well I know - I knowed men as I always thoug
ht I were a little bit above 'em for the reason of this I thought I'd had a better bringing up than what He had, you understand me there, get me straight. Because I knew what his father and mother had treated his - him, you understand me and different way
s
 I'd been treated with being clothes as I always thought I were a little bit above him. That; I did get that opinion and it stuck in me mind and today I fancy I still have that little bit of feeling with me. As - the somewhat - I thinks well, I - I'm a lo
t
 better than them. Oh yes, I have that feeling at present. Because I'm thinking with how I were brought up I were always brought to try and do me best for every - for everybody, and try get as good - much out of life as I could and which I - I have done a
nd through that it's made me think as I'm a little bet - a little bit better than a lot of people I know. See a lot of people I know what goes drinking a lot. They go bingoing. Now, we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 didn
\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 . We don't go in pubs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 If I wanted a drink I'd go in a drink, and 
have a drink but with me - we never think about it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So I do think I'm a little bit better graded than a lot of people I know what were lads when I were lads.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Prior to 1918 what sort of people belonged to the same class that you'd put yourself in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - how it - how it comes about like as you saw it in your life you saw some - some people, they didn't bother how they went out how they were clothes or anything like that, they were just rough and - that's how I put it. As I - they'd walk on say on
e side and there were a barbed fence between us. I didn't want mix with them because I were only getting in trouble and I knew what expect when I got to t'other side you see so I didn't bother with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you then think there were two classes of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Definitely, yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What sort of people would you say belonged to the other group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Them what - what belonged to - to t'other group as I thought as I didn't belong to. Well their whereabouts and the way they lived, the 
way they dressed and they way they spent money is what - I - objected to. And - girls - like - being - insulting girls or one thing or another you see, that's what I - and I saw it and it made me - on me guard for it you see. Because I hadn't been brought
 up that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Could you see any common factors between you and the other people like you on the one hand and common features amongst the other group of people, either by occupation or where they lived or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - yes. Well a lot
 of that went on - you'd see you'd some friends you know like, oh well, they live up Chorley Old Road, you live in Bashall Street, these names of street round about you understand. Now Bashall street was a street what - at that time there was - there was 
blackies living in't' street, now I'm bringing this in, these was first lot of blackies in Bolton and they were called Cole}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 , C
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 ley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407  their names was Coley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and - their houses wasn't kept up to a standard, their curtains, their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15234102\charrsid14966407 mopping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 outside of the steps, yo
u understand me, and the dress of the people in the locality. You see? And that's we thought if you went round Bashall Street, oh - that were - weren't Victory, that were slum round Victory - they called it Victory round there you see, that were slum and 
if there were any trouble about you could always bet it come from round there. You could nearly always be sure on that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I don't think so. I think that was - h
ow I got that, I don't know where I got it from but that's how I got it, I can't tell you but I did start thinking I were a - little bit above some of 'em you see. Like, from leaving school I - I got that in and how it come into me head that was th'only r
eason I can see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another, your sisters }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 curtseying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  to important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, I can -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You touching your cap to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. I always respected that, in - in fact I do it today. To people I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Who }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 you would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  be taught to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well, me mother and me dad always used to - make you understand anybody what were older than you - bit older, you know, lot older than you - you always had to show respect by wi
shing 'em time of day and raising your hat. And then sometimes like when I was just started knocking about, we had bowler hats then you see, well I were always told by me dad when you had a bowler hat on you had to lift if off your head but if you had a c
ap on you'd to touch your cap. Now me - I were told that with me - with me brothers and me sisters and - me dad and me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was there anybody in particular that you had to pay special respect to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, I never - it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 The clergy or anybody like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh well - when you - you met, like your minister at church you were always on your best behaviour like you was cautioned about that and you knew it and you choose everything - words you said and what you did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have to call anybody sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh - no. Only at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you remember anybody showing respect to your mother or father in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Apart from within your own family I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no. No. No, they all - no, I can't remember 'em showing any more respect than anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Who would be considered the most important people in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 In 't' district? You speaking like now, at time, well we used think important man in town like in Chorley Old Road were Vicar, old
 - Hayes, he were called Hayes. And Doctor Patchet, he were t'old doctor now, they were important people like, we thought they were because with politics or anything like that we didn't - me dad never had any inclination about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Why do you think that they were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well you depended on your doctor for your health and you're your bringing up you depended a lot on a vicar. To show you lights after your father and mother had shown you. If you had anything - say any
thing you didn't want to discuss with your mother and father there was always there to help you, and it's same at the present day, if people only knew it. But a lot of people today don't realise it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about the shopkeepers in the area, who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh I can't answer you that, who they associate with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Had you any small shops round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. when I were a youngster. They had little shops, like I had me grandmother in Nile Street had a little shop. Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What sort of a shop was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well it were - you bought - you bought anything. Ha'porth of tea and sugar, home made flour cakes and that. In fact, she brought her a matter of about seven houses out of shop.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes, now about this shop you see, 
me grandmother had. It were - it was just one house window and it - she built and built 'til she bought a house over across and had a big shop window made of it you see, and you could buy anything you wanted. Even take your clogs and have 'em ironed there
.
 There were a lot what they called tic going on then, you understand, that was you got stuff and you paid at weekend. And that's how I think me grandmother made bit of money she did do with - having strap customers and ha'porth of this and you ran a bill 
on weekend, you went and paid it, you'd money then, you had tic again for week and it were like that. That were me grandmother and she did a lot to - her own baking and that. Because they had a big family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What system of reckoning for keeping track did she use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I can't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 tell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  you that. I don't know that. But I know when - when she died there were about fourteen houses in Nile Street what belonged to her and then - me mother was th'oldest one and then there was divided by like and every 
quarter they had been draw money off them you see and - they kept on 'til they were all pulled down, demolished. And in fact when they were sold they got twenty-five pound a piece for them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 
That was in - not long - well, since Nile Street were pulled down 
but that were experience that and it were showing years in them days you started with nothing, you - and you had a bit of go about you , you could - build yourself, but you'd have to work for it, oh yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And your grandparents achieved this by your grandfather }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 working}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and your grandmother having the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Having shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Which do you think contributed most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I think - I think shop did. Because way I've been told with me mother in days gone by, with me grandfather a tinplate worker
 and worked probably a fortnight you see, and then at money he wouldn't go work, he'd have a week off and he'd be going in pub }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 backward}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and forward having nothing to eat hardly, then when he'd spent his money, bear in mind, beer very cheap me then, as they tell me you could get a pint for ha'penny or a penny and - when he was skint he went back work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 It wasn't because he was laid off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, no. He went to spend his money what he'd saved. And he wanted spend it that way with some of his mates what used go in pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Could it be then that your grandmother started the shop as a security?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
That were - that was - that was reason one - I think that was one of reasons. And - she had her daughters with her, in fact she had - she put one - to one o
f her daughters to teaching at Pikes Lane school. I'm speaking a long while ago now that. And - then she put me uncles, one were a weaver, one worked in foundry and t'others was - me aunt - me aunt were a weaver and me mother worked in 't' mill, I don't k
n
ow what it were, jack-framer or something like that, but they all had to work and I think was money she bought these few houses with. And I think when it were all divided I think it divided in six, there were six of 'em, and then we used to get it every q
u
arter you see. And - then it were divided by five of my - my - with me sisters and brothers you see, divided with us and then - then - now me - I had a sister what had plenty of money, me other sister had, they didn't - they'd no need this money if they d
i
dn't want it, but they always used take it. Now I were in need of it at time but they never used say, well here, have mine. It were always equally divided in my family like, in ours you see, but when the houses were sold I think it ran out as me wife coul
d afford buy a pair of curtains out of houses when they was finished.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you know what sort of people the clergy would associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What - clergy what? Well - round - Great Lever - there was St Marks and they'd a really good vicar there. And 
they'd a good vicar at Trinity. And they used to go round and go round to people, you understand me, and they were up Chorley Old Road, they were St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 Luke\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 . Now I think he were Mr Dearden and he used to go round a lot. They did a lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 visiting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  vicars in 
them days. More than what they do today. Now they might not like me saying that but in my experience they did. But still today anybody ever wanted a vicar, young or old, they'd come and see you straight away. Now I've had experience with vicars - I've wor
ked with old vicars and I've worked with young 'uns and there's not a lot of difference with visiting. There's not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Who would they regard as the sort of people that they would be friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh well, now that is a really, you know, you're just
 asking some really - snorters. Well you'd always find out as - a lot of vicars, you're smiling while I'm telling you this, they always have a certain class of people what they go to if they wanted anything for church, you understand me. And they get it. 
T
hey always had a smooth way of getting it but yet they wouldn't forget the people who had nothing. But they'd lean a little bit to them where they thought they could improve the church with, I'll put it that way. But they always liked seeing you there at 
Sundays, rich or poor, and it happens today same, in my opinion. In }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 today\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Who would the teachers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 The day school teachers? Well - I'm only speaking of what I know with me own aunt what were a teacher and - you wouldn't see her me
ssing a lot with a lot of mil, girls you understand me. When they were wearing clogs this aunt of mine always have shoes on and always dressed to kill, you understand. Where you'd see me other aunt what - two sisters living together - you'd see her with h
e
r striped underskirt on, but you'd never see me aunt - other aunt - with her underskirt like that, always dressed smartly and I think they all - there were a distinction in teachers. Now - in my time of schooling now I can mention you names like, I can me
n
tion you two, Mr McCann and Mr Fishley was a teacher. Now they'd go and have a drink with any of men in 't' - in 't' pub. They wasn't like stand-offs, they'd mix with the people. And your own father and mother knew it and they never objected to it. And if
 there were any trouble going on at school your father knew. Because it had come from them. Oh aye, it were all handed down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you think the men teachers mixed more freely than the women teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well, you see, with me being a lad we were only
 men taken at footballing, men used take you to baths and - take you playing cricket. You'd more association with - with men than what - like lady teachers they were more teaching with girls and showing 'em - they did take boys for drawing and one thing o
r another and that but there were that - I thought were a man teacher you were more obedient with him than what you was with a - a lady teacher. Now I might have been wrong but you could take a few liberties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I was meaning did they mix more with adults, you say these two gentlemen used to go and have a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 But your aunt wouldn't associate with the mill girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - this aunt of mine -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I wondered if you meant the men would have mixed more readily or whether this was just an isolated instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
With - well I - I think now I'm just speaking of this aunt now, you'll never see her like - going to Grand, you understand me. She'd always be going somewhere else you see, going to different meetings and one thing or another
. As she didn't seem to have enough time to - have friends, going - mill girls going in to their house you understand, where me other aunt had friends come in and when here friends were here this other aunt what were teacher wouldn't be in. You see. But w
hen she had some friends come in to me grandmother's these others - this other aunt wouldn't be in with her friends. And you could see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would they be a different class of friends anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. A different class of friends completely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What sort of people would the teacher-aunt's friends be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - they'd be more - round - Green Lane style, you see, like - bit stand-offish, bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 snobbish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 . And - that was it you see. Like I fancy this aunt of mine used speak to these mill girls if she met '
em out like pass time of day but I don't think she'd - she'd association with like any games or anything like that - to - to always to me to my as I can recollect her she was always so prig neat, you understand, everything were perfect, in her appearance 
and everything. That's now I find it out with - two different classes of teacher, a lady teacher and a man teacher. Now some of 'em might have been standy-off but I - these particular two men comes in me mind very plain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would there be any employers living in the district for you to know what sort of people they would knock around with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, there were no employers in - in't' street, in our - where I - where I lived. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there any that you knew that lived elsewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 People you knew fairly well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
We used - knowed 'em very well indeed. There was a - there were only one man firms you understand. There was growing. There was a little foundry called Morris what started making - working at nights and making number
 plates for when motor cars started. He was one of first and he made 'em of aluminuim. Now he had one - he had a house and he turned it into a little moulding shop. At present time now he's got - he's got a foundry up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 Dubhill}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 , well and coming down for his 
sons is taking over you understand and it's doing well. Now there were firelight business. Halliwells. Now we knew them very well. Now unfortunate they couldn't insure firelight business and not long ago, say five years ago, his works got burn - burned do
wn to ground, well he wasn't covered with insurance. Now that - that business is gone completely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 But you knew these people when you were quite young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I knew 'em personally well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was this because you came in contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I c
ame in contact to 'em through schooling, knowing 'em at school and - their fathers knowed my relations and that's how I - and they went St Marks school and that's how I got to know and we - well I've been to their houses, they've been to our house you see
.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 They mixed quite freely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Freely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about farmers, would there be any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Farmers? Oh well, you'd have go top of Great Lever for that else round Barrow Bridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would you know any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, I never knowed any farmer
s. For one of reasons we didn't know you see, my mother and father believed - believers of stores. Well they bought their milk off stores. You see, so they got divvy on it, they didn't bother with farmers 'cos farmers didn't pay any divvy. You see, if - t
racking everything back it all works within one another. You see, a shop where you could get the best and get a return for it, that were their idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What sort of people would you say went to the church, I'd like to distinguish between the different typ
es of church, Church of England, Catholic and Non-conformist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Yes. Well - well I'm just speaking of one church in particular. Now what I know very well. Now that was Holy Trinity. Now there was always, see there was Holy Trinity church and Coe Street
 Mission. Now - all big noises went to church. Now when anything were going on at mission you could rely on the big noises coming helping mission out and you could rely on poorer class, that's same as our lot, if church wanted any help - helping them. Now
 
speaking of a - that's in church of England. Now speaking of Catholics, now I've no - never had any dealings with 'em, only I used mate with two of 'em, there was three of us mated together when we getting a bit older. Now them two Catholics always kept b
y theirself but there was always three of us. That was me and I was - th'outer man kind of thing. Now in a congregation, now I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 a congregation you see, in which me wife were a Sunday school teacher. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 Now I found out there as you - they were a clique, 
you see, well fortunate for me wife and her brothers was in the clique so I automatically fell in the clique but it'd had took me a long, long while to get in that if I could ever have got in you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And that's what I think about religion. But speaking of
 - well we don't want to talk about like services being conduct or anything like that but you always find out as - a congregational hymn is more swing about it than what our own Church of England, and you can get your teeth into it, you know, you can - yo
u can sing and enjoy it. That's what I think about religion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you think there were any different degrees of sincerity in attending church and so on at the different churches?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - there might have been, there might have been. Now, speaking o
f - Chorley Road Conge - a lot of boys and girls in my time, I went Sunday school and Young }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 Men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 class, it weren't what you were being taught. It were - well you'd go to your eye on a girl you see. And - naturally it pulled you that way and - I found out 
it - it went to a lot - places like that. I can remember another case of a fellow what left one church and he went Chorley Road Conge because he went with this girl. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 
And Scout - a Scout Master there left St Luke's to go to Chorley Road Conge because his girl were Scout Mistress, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Like pulls either way, just - I don't think there are a lot of people you know is really sincere and there's a lot - what just goes - I go church. It's not going - going church, anybody can go church, but it's taking the in
terest in it. I can go now sometimes and I can't get interested in his service. When he's preaching. Other times I'm delighted I - you could hear a pin drop but it - you find it, a spasm'll come over you, he'll just say something what you want t'hear and 
something what - your mind's wandering instead of going - you'll find it that way. Now take - now we'll just speak about this new Con - Communion. D'you want speak about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You've spoken about people drinking and spending their money in different wa
ys, would you say that all people in the same category as yourself had the same standard of living or would they have different standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, you'd find different standard of living, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would there be particularly poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 There'd mix - be a mixed bottle. Yes, you'd have - you'd find that standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Are there any particular families that you can think off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. I can mention you - some families as I know, you know, what - is over the line completely, because they hadn't bee
n - taught a - right way. Now I know people what goes drinking with their fathers, goes drinking with their mothers, you understand me. Well they've got over the line where if - if the people, their fathers had have taught 'em different and wouldn't have 
gone with 'em it'd have stopped them from going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you think that any group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Any group superior? No, I don't think so. No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I think you've implied that some families were thought of as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 rough}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you remember a distinction being felt between and craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - from he being a craftsman, that was in me own trade, and a labourer in - in a - in iron foundry, a craftsman, a 
moulder treated a labourer as th'under dog. It were reach me, fetch me, bring me, carry me. And you - you always thought in your trade you were a better man than him, but when you got outside - a lot of people was on 't' same level. And they was treated o
n
 't' same level. Like you'd go and have a drink with 'em, have a cigarette with 'em. But in - when they was in the trade they was - you were a little bit above them 'cos you were a bit - you were a bit station better in life. They'd not been taught the tr
ade, they were just do as you told them. Oh yes, there's distinguishing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 But it didn't apply so much in practical matters outside the actual work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, no. No, they was all - it all be - they all were nearly one footing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
No. No. I just think as me mother - was ordinary working woman and she were - she always classed herself as same as anybody else. No better or no worse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You've spoken about these one man small firms where they've grown and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would you say then that it was possible for people to move from one social class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes. It depends on your ability.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Can you remember there being anybody who was described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
As a real gentleman? Yes. A real gentleman. I meet him yet now you know and he is a real good liver and he wouldn't do nobody any harm. He's real gentleman. I can tell you that about - I'll not mentio
n his name but - he'd do a good turn for anybody and he classes everybody on same level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And this was somebody you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And it was because he would do anything for anybody that you would regard his as a real gentleman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 As a real gentleman or a real man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You mentioned the policeman earlier on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was there one around where you actually lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 A policeman? 'H yes. Old Bobby Brookes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did I - well in them days y
ou see old Bobby Brookes, he were an old soldier when he came - I'll tell you his life story, it won't be long. And - if there were anything going on at Town Hall he was always on Town Hall steps with all his medals across. You'd see him on Valley Bowling
 Green, up Chorley Old Road, when he weren't on duty having a pint or two with anybody. When he were on night duty going in Sally Upsteps, at middle at night, in'tp back, were always bottles for him. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 He were a real walloper. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That were old Bobby Brookes. He 
were got - had his job mostly because he were an old soldier and he had a lot of medals and - he had no talent with him. There were no talent with him, he was just country bobby kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you were naughty as a child did your mother ever say that she'd call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, it were mostly Blackman. It were mostly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 Blackman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 , not bobby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What actually was the threat then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Now you'll not be a good lad I'll bring black man. Oh aye, it weren't bobby. Mostly black man as I can remem
ber me mother telling me. 'Cos you didn't see a lot of black people at that - in Bolton at that time, and there was only one family in my younger days and that were Culeys family up Victory, in Bashall Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you think that the policeman treated people fairly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do I think they're fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 This particular one that you knew, Bobby Brookes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh - no, it were a just a time of getting - getting his time over, getting on 't' pension. Oh no, he'd -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did he treat people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well he 
treat - treat 'em all right you know but - he'd - everything were always quiet when he were about, you could always rely on everything being quiet. But he - he'd have a drink with anybody and he'd associate with you. Oh yes, he - no faults like that with 
him. Everything were quiet when he were around. And he'd give you, big or little he'd have a go at you and he'd - he'd always come off top of - top of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 tree}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 . He were well known in Bolton, Bobby Brookes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was your home rented or did you own it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Rented. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes. It were nearly always Friday night, coincidence asking that. Pay day. Really hot, I think myself nearly all your insurance men, nearly tried get round either Friday night, Saturday morning or first thing Monday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did you feel about your landlord, was he a good landlord, could you get things done that needed doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - we all - back in them thought they were fair, me mother must have thought it were fair 'cos she nev
er complained but - me dad'd do - and me brothers 'd say we'd do a bit of beautifying, a bit of painting and that, we did - well they did it for your own benefit not for - for landlord's benefit, he got the benefit of it but you wanted make your house - s
omething like so you did a little bit on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What if there was anything structural that needed attending to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well he'd - landlord'd do it, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You didn't have any difficulty about getting him to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 We never - oh no. Well in the
m th'houses we lived in they'd been good houses. Good firm houses and most things what's been wanted doing was - doing your own painting and - putting some paper on walls. There were no whitewash, I can tell you that. We had no places whitewashed and I've
 been in some houses where the kitchens were whitewashed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh we had a struggle. Oh yes. Anybody today bringing a family up and in them days had a struggle. It's one big s
truggle bringing a family up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you conscious of this struggle as a small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
No. I'm never conscious of it, it's only after effects as I realise after. Because it seemed to me as when I were a - a young lad if I wanted anything, say any; toffees, a bit of persuading to me mother and I got it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Of course you were fortunate in being the youngest member of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That was one of reasons, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you know if it made any different to the family if your father was ill and off work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - asking a question like that now I - I can't remember me father ever - now even what I'm saying now - ever being off work. Only when he was - last two year of his life. I've seen me dad at sixty putting iron file and filing his own teet
h, he'd not a tooth out of his head and he had his hair cut every fortnight with number ought clippers - a big fellow he was. But I never know him be ill, only me mother. Me mother had - later on in life was deaf and she had a bad heart, that - but that w
ere later on in life like with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you know if your parents ever had to get financial help from anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. They never had. Because as I told you before, me father always very lucky in keeping employed. At knights and Woods where he served h
is time and then he went to Hicks and he were made under foreman, and he was very fortunate in keeping in work, bear in mind the wage wasn't big but - he was very fortunate. Very fortunate indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And I imagine he would be a rather sort of an independent man anyway wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - he had his friends, you understand, and if he'd have - if he'd have made himself independent he'd have been better off than what he finished up at. You see, he liked going having a drink at Saturday dinner time with
 his mates in foundry. Where if he'd have kept - left that side along and kept on t'other side and gone with foremen he'd improved himself. But he got on that - he got as far as he wanted go, he didn't want go any step higher where he could have gone high
er but he never made any attempt. Because he wanted be with his - pals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were you given lessons at all by your parents or a tutor or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, th'only thing I was - I were learnt to helped to learn to read with my mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Before you went to school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no. When I started learning I were helped with me mother and father and doing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 sums}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 . I did 'em at home and me mother or me father and me sisters checked 'em up on a slate. There were slates then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Five year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you first started what time in the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Nine o'clock 'til twelve. And then I think it was quarter to two to four o'clock. In t'infants that 
was like you know. And then it used to go same time at morning when we went out of th'infants to quarter past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What sort of a school was it, a church or board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I went to a Church of England School, St Marks at beginning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 That was in the infants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. And then I went to Gaskell Street Council school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was that after you'd finished with the infants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. When I - and we went like - we went live in that - farther on you see, we removed so I - we went to nearest school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were these both mixed schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did boys and girls have lessons together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 In the same classrooms. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you were going to St Marks you'd be living in Nile Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 In Nile Street, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did you get to school, how far was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh - ten minutes walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You would walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Who went with you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I - I went with me brother and a sister were going same school at same time. Me mother didn't - me mother only took me for beginnin
g and then she dropped off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you go home for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well - tell you truth, I can't give you any idea of it, only - enjoyed it and - I - Miss Leason were t'headmistress, you know, that's - th
ey learnt em what I wanted. I never broke any pots at school, I were never at top of any class but I always holded me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 I respected 'em. I really did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there some that you specially like or disliked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. I liked 'em all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they emphasise things as important, things like manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes, yes, then they did, yes, honestly. You had try keep your - I remember picking old paper - picking a lot of papers up you know at scho
ol, being told and being clean, having me hands clean when we're having our writing books. And you didn't have any writing books 'til I were nearly leaving infants you see. It were always on slates you understand. But I can remember us - seeing us having 
our hands washed, Miss Taylor were one at - like getting one of teachers, one of big teachers you see, as what was you was learning like, at first you was only kind of playing about you know kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they bother about the way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I don't think so, they never seemed to bother you know at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 If you did something that the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You'd get the stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Whatever the offence?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, no, no.
 No, let's be fair now. I've been stood at back at - in't' corner, I've been stood at black of blackboard. And I've had stick. But - when you got stick you - you must have need it, that were my idea. Since I've realised, like little bits of pranks, for ta
lking or anything you'd get shoved in the corner. And you daren't - you don't turn round 'til she told you. Oh aye, that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So it would be a fairly serious offence to get the stick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You'd get stick, yes. No messing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was that from the teacher in the class or the head?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
You'd get it off teacher in class. It were only when I were getting round about twelve to fourteen as they were being sent to t'headmaster. For stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 This would be in the Gaskell Street school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes, the Gaskell Street school there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Going on to the Gaskell Street school, where were you living then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 We were living in Wentworth Street. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh - ten minutes - you could get there in five minutes, ten minutes at most.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, went on me own. Me mother took meat first time like. Then I went on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You still had your dinner at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did you think about Gaskell Street, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Ye
s. I liked it. It were - it were a good school, were a big school and they were good men teachers and they were ladies teachers and they'd a good headmaster, a fellow called Mr Smith. Now Mr Smith was headmaster at St Marks. I were never under him, he was
 in the big school you see, and then he - but I knew he were t'headmaster at St Marks when I went to Gaskell Street you see. He'd taught me, me brothers and me sisters there you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did the teachers at Gaskell Street emphasise particular things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Yes, they were a bit keen on your - on your - you know, keeping yourself tidy and then I remember going on strike at school. Yes. At Gaskell Street school. Over Mr Ferrowhall giving one of lads stick and - round fourteen 
mark then you see, I were four - getting ready for leaving. And he were cock at school, he were boss of school and he'd had stick he said for something for nothing so he got us all go on strike and we went at - went back school at dinner time and then whe
n
 whistle blew were about a dozen of us went on Mere Hall Park and we stayed there 'til Mr Fenhall, Mr Smith and Mr Roskill came to school and brought us in and we all got four raps a piece and our name in black book. That were at Gaskell Street. Aye. That
's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How long did your strike last then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh - we was back in there before playtime. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 
Soon as they knowed we - we weren't in class they were up for us. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And soon as we saw 'em, well we were all - shaking. Wonder what }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 we're}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  going to get at t'other en
d. Were we going to get a letter for take home to our parents and that. But we got four raps and we got 'em off Mr Smith in his office and they were really conkers, you blew your hands when you'd had 'em. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 But - that jettied you up you know, but - a young lad about that age you know, they want a bit of jacking and th'only thing what jettied 'em up were getting stick.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did girls get the same sort of punishment as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh well I couldn't answer you that because I never took on - a lot of notice of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Your parents helped you with your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they take a keen interest in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 They took a bit of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 interest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  - if I were a bit stuck and I'd either ask me sisters and me brothers and me mother and me dad. And - me dad'
d have me reading for him sometimes out of paper. See how I were going on. And me mother'd be listening but she were a bit deaf like but he'd have me reading and - he'd pull me up a time or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they used to ask you what you'd been doing at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. They asked - asked us time and time again like what we'd been doing and - all about what we were doing at school and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they visit the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. I can't remember any - any time in my schooldays ever being a parents evening like they have today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did they meet your teachers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Not as I can recollect. No. I can't remember 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did the other children come from similar types of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Somewhere round it. Somewhere round it. Same as in
't' school there were a rough lot and a quiet lot. Like having a bit of a - set to an school yard and then you'd get stick, were always that going on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there definite sort of gangs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Gangs, yes. Yes, there were gangs in school like -
 like there - him what were over school, Adamson his name was, he were a big lad. Now everybody were frightened to death of him and what he said you did. That were reason we went on strike }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 
through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did the teachers single out some of the children for special treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Yes. Now I can remember one - one lad what was bad at speaking. And they used - he used go somewhere once a week to - make his words come out flowing to him you see and Mr Smith used take a bit of interest in that lad, yes. His
 name were Parkinson. I remember him quite well. Now that lad, he's a - he were a spinner. He's a spinner - well he's living now. I've - I've seen him knocking around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did any of the children seem to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh they might be you k
now like - they might have been and bits of things going on Empire Day like you always went in school yard and - you all sung, piano were took out in school yard and you - you sung. Then I remember being in a play one time in school at Gaskell Street and 
i
t were Christopher Columbus. And a pal what - a waterman now - me and him were a wave, that were part our play on me hands and knees waving about, we were supposed to be waves. Oh aye. You're laughing though that's real. You know, it were - had a good lif
e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you go on to another school after Gaskell Street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. That was the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 If you'd have had the opportunity for more schooling would you have taken it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, I wanted go working. I wanted go working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you attend any part time classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. When I left school I left. Because all me friends were working and I wanted be with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes. I've regrets about it.
 Not from leaving school like, from regrets from starting working to present time I've regrets. I wish I'd have gone night school. But - I was too busy with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So you would like to attend night school if you'd your time to come over again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 While you were at school did you ever have a part time job to earn a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 We come now to your first full time job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Moulding. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And it was at Hick Hargreaves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Hick and Hargreaves.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did I get to foundry. On - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 on t'tram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  cars - tram cars not buses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did you get the job in the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I got it through me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When you first went there what exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well I was only lad in shop like, going and brewing tea at breakfast time. We started work at six o'clock at morning 'til eight o'clock, and then from eight o'c
lock to half past was breakfast time. Well lads then, shop lads they called him had to go and brew tea for all men, you see, and if a man was bringing egg you see, you'd put his egg in his can and put it in his tea and warm it up that way. Well if you had
 
a - if yours were a bigger egg than what mine were I'd run your name off your egg and put mine name on my egg, them was tricks what they did. You understand. And then you brewed up for them at dinner time. And you worked 'til five o'clock at - at night, y
ou'd an hour for your dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about the hours on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Six o'clock 'til twelve. Now lads used to have to clean all the moulding shop up, collect all the spades and oil 'em and you worked an hour longer, so you worked 'til one. But that was like overtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You wouldn't work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was there a half day - Saturday would be the half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Saturday were the half day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you have any holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, th'ordinary Bolton holiday week like and Septembe
r holidays, Christmas, New Years Day, Christmas Day. Easter, I think, Good Friday, it think it was Good Friday and then two days at Easter - at Easter and a week at Bolton holiday week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were these paid holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 They were all unpaid?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 There were nothing paid for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What were you paid, you told me you got ten shillings at twenty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. That was spending money that was. Yes. When I started working I got seven and six a week for fifty-two hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 At that time did you feel that it was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh well I never took any notice of that like. I only - realised that as I'm growing on. And then you got a rise every twelve month you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 To me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Intact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, never touched it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 She gave you some back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 She gave me some spending money back. Now me first week of spending money was sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Then your spending money grew as your wage grew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Grew as me wage grew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What did you spend your spending money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh well, all sorts of things, I can't just pictures and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You wouldn't be spending it all on toffee at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, no, it'd be pictures and that. You could - you could go to football ma
tch for sixpence then you know, go see Bolton Wanderers Saturday afternoon. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did You get on with the other people that you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Very well. Very well indeed. Up - you see, up to me getting up to about eighteen like you was maki
ng bits of jobs and learning and I went working with one man, fellow called Tommy Hilton, he were a friend of me dad's you see and you were only a lad or you was only treated as a lad and we were making a big tank at time and he was stood on top of a big 
b
ox and I were throwing sand from floor onto top of box and it was hard work and - he told me to hurry up and I was really hard - sweating with it and I called him a lazy devil. Come down and help me throw some on. And I had to run out of foundry after 'co
s he'd have got hold of me he'd have give me a good hiding. But he told me dad about it, then when me dad saw me he told me he said, now when he ever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 asks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  you do anything never answer him back. And I were nearly eighteen year old then. So that were in a foundry.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Were there many young boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh yes, there were about a dozen of us all in different ages, you see, as you left from being shop lad you went a little bit higher, then you went a little bit higher 'til you were top lad. Well you were nearly
 - you were nearly - you'd turned twenty then you see. So at Sat'days, instead of you doing any work at Sat'day you sat on bosses steps and you told t'other lads for collect all spades but you got your hour overtime just same, 'cos you were in charge of l
ads you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You served a proper apprenticeship didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Seven year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 When did that start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 From fourteen. Yes. To being twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did you feel that your employer treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well he were - he were a good forema
n I can rest you assure on that and - he leaned you and you learned your trade, it were a well noted place to learn as when you - if you serve your time at Hicks you could have gone being a moulder anywhere. They were a good foremen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did the management of the firm treat their employees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well they seemed to treat you all right you know, there was never no - grumbles or anything. We had a strike one time when I were in - getting on in me years then like. I was serving me time and - oh I couldn't grumble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Well it were a good class of work. A really good class of work, you know, engineering work. It wasn't just making fire bottoms and - and down spouts and things like that, you'd a good variety and it were good class work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 There'd be quality and specification about it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Yes. Well it was noted - Hick and Hargreaves was noted if you worked there you could go to any foundry in country and hold your won with any of moulders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You said you enjoyed the work didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You worked your way up didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you stay on at Hick Hargreaves all your working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no. 'Til I was twenty-one. Then when your twenty-one you come on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 
journeyman\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  money you see. Well 
you - you started on ten shilling a week under journeys money 'til you become twenty-two, and then you got full money. But I could have left at twenty-one and gone to another foundry and got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 
journeyman\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  money you see. And then gone back to Hicks under twelve month and claimed }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 journeyman\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  money, you see. In which it weren't - it weren't a lot at time. I think - when I came out of me time I think wage was two pound - two pound ten. That were for fifty-two hours a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 So what did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 We
ll, you was classed a man then, you had to do a fair days work, you understand. Boss'd come round and give you a job and you'd have to make it you see. That was your - because you was a full-blown moulder then you see, so what he give you you had to make 
it. And you couldn't make it you had to get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was this still at Hicks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I was - twenty-two year old and we come on short time. So me being one of young 'uns, you follow me, they were playing wee
ks about. Like you work a week, play a week, so then after it come as you worked a week and played a fortnight. You see. So I got fed-up with that. And - I got in - in touch with a fellow at Bury and I went to Bentley and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 Jackson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  at Bury and I worked the
re thirteen - thirteen month. In Lord Street that were at Bury. Now they were on a bonus system. As you could make more money than what you made you got more money with it. You see? You got a bit extra. Then I come and got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 . You see? Got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  abo
ut when I were - nearly twenty-three, or twenty-three I think it were. Well then I had to get money then. Had to work. Well it - trade was very - very bad then. And then I got this - they went slack at Bentley and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 Jackson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  and then I got a job back at Hic
ks, Hick and Hargreaves. And then they went slack again at Hicks and dole sent me to Harry Owens at Atherton, another moulding place. Now I worked there twenty-three - twenty-two year. As I become leading hand there at that foundry, with about five bob a 
w
eek more than what t'others did, that were all I got, you see. And then when war started then we - while I were there and then I got fed-up at - well I worked nine - nine and a half hours a day at Harry Owens, then we played Sat'day morning you see, so at
 Sat'day morning, to get a little bit more money, wage at that time was two pound nineteen and elevenpence I brought home and I were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
, understand me. Well - and I had a young - two youngsters. You see, well I had to make more money so at St'day morning I used go out cutting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 lawns}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 I used go and cut me sister's lawn and do a bit of gardening at Sat'days, up to about four o'clock.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 But you've stayed in moulding all your working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 All me life. Yes. Bar one bad spell. And it was - it were really bad spell all in Lancashire for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 foundries}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 and me brother-in-law were a manager of a mill and he said, if you want a job I'll find you a job labouring in mill. Well it were better money than what it were being on dole 'cos at that time there was - I g
ot half a crown a piece for me children so I took this job at Walkden, working in mill labouring you see and I worked there - oh, six month 'til the job had finished and then I got a job back at Harry Owens foundry at Atherton and I stayed there then 'toi
l I come - I finished up at Wadsworths at High Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you retire from Wadsworths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
No, I went caretaking then. I started with rheumatics in me knees and I was - we was looking after Coe Street Mission - mother was and I was like, keeping it c
lean and looking after boiler. And then I got fed-up of traveling you see and I were - started this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 rheumatic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 and lumbago I were being plagued with, so I came out of foundry and I went caretaking. And I finished up caretaking - at Holy Trinity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Moulding was really your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes, that was most me - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you belong to the trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you take an active part in it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well I only was shop steward, that were all. It wasn't active part, it was just seeing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  men paid their club money and that, so it were no active part in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you feel that the employers and the workers had the same outlook or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Well - at Harry - at Harry Owe
ns at Atherton it were a one man firm. He'd built up from, his father had built the foundry up from nothing, you understand, and it was really a good foundry. And he were a man what made you work. If you'd anything went wrong you got a good cussing but he
 
never took any malice, when he'd cuss you - he'd forgot it. But it never happened again and he were a chap like go in at morning at half past six, he were th'owner of foundry but he'd be in foundry at half past six and he'd be in there 'til eight o'clock,
 you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about at Hicks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 At Hicks? Oh well, you - you started work then at half past six - at six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you feel that the management and the workers had the same outlook there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no. No. You worked a lot - a lot harder at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 Harry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  Owens than what you did at Hicks. Because I was working for me job. If you didn't work hard and you come slack you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 were'nt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  on't' dole so it made you as you worked hard and you did your best. You knew you were good - kept on for a bit. Then at one pe
riod he went slack at Harry Owens so at Monday night he stopped about seven of us, like, he gave us our cards so I went to dole and it were club night and a fellow called Jimmy Keith was sick with shop steward then and he - they wanted some men at Plank L
a
ne foundry, that were in Leigh, that was farther you see. So he - I gets a letter from th' unemployment to go and see 'em at Plank Lane foundry as there were a job there. I went. And I got the job. So I went back to Harry Owens to tell him I were going Pl
a
nk Lane. Well I told him at Plank Lane, I said, now Harry Owen pays me sixpence a day - extra in bus fare you see. Oh well, he says, I can't, he said, but - it'd cost me a shilling a day going there you see. So he said, I'll tell you what I'll do with you
,
 I'll pay you sixpence a day up to Plank Lane foundry - up to Punch Bowl and then from Punch Bowl to Atherton it were another sixpence return you see. So I went back to Harry Owens and told him so he said, well leave the tools here and pick 'em up at morn
ing, you see. I said, all right. So when I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 went back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 at morning like for got to Plank Lane starting Harry Owens in foundry at half past six, he says, where't' going? I said, I'm going Plank Lane, you know where I'm going. She says, get your jacket off and s
tart. So instead of going Plank Lane I stopped at Harry Owens. That was at Wednesday. And at Friday he stopped three more men and kept me on. You understand me. And I never - played me after. That were let - let him see you see as other people'd take you 
on. He thought, oh well, he's got you booked. When he wants you to work you work. It were hard life - bringing a family up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Would you say that starting full time work changed your attitude towards life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Later on in life it did. When I became to 
having responsibilities put on me. Then, I saw the change in life and I saw it quick. For the reason, we had a youngster you see, we were champion when we got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 , doing well, youngster came along and - we were doing champion then, I started short time
 and bit of money we'd saved up me and me wife kept tribbling away, tribbling away, tribbling away. Because I were only getting twenty-eight shilling for me wife and two children. So we - had to work to try to keep your job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Going back to when you first started work, you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 continued}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did starting work affect your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 What about your relationship with your brothers and sisters, did that change at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, no. I were just put on same }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 basis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  as t'tothers, they - I were working and taking me money home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you spend your Sunday any differently, was this the point at which you started dropping off going to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes, that's - started dropping off then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was this the period when you began to take an interest in politics or was it not 'til later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Later on. Later on. I never took a lot of interest in politics you know but - I read papers and what I thought were right well we'll - well give 'em a chance, give '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6690923\charrsid14966407 em a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407  trial.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You became a Labour man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Me wife as well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Was that the way you voted at the elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you do anything for the party?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same sort of way as before or did you start doing different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Like when I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11498930 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 No, when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh well - well we started with - gang, I went with a gang of lads you know and - we spent our nights - and we
 got bikes and we went rides and one thing and another and footballing. We got a football team up and - no, I don't think it changed anything. Only I went with this gang and we all ganged together. That were reasons of dropping of - like going Sunday scho
ol and that were dropped off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you make any new friends when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes, I made a lot of friends at work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did you make any girl friends about that time as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. I met my wife. Soon on in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You took your friends home didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh I'd take me friends but I didn't take any girls home. Oh no. I'd have got shot. Oh no, I could take lads home but I couldn't take girls home. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Did your parents know you were friendly with girls as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
Oh well - later on like they got to know like. I - went to pictures at Saturday night like. Well at Olympia you see you went to pictures - you went at Friday night by rights looking at pictures and then Saturday night you went scrounging 
round see what - any girls what you could - take home and - that's where I - met me wife. But I'd knowed }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12983912\charrsid14966407 her}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 
 a long while before that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 How old were you before you felt you could take her home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Take her home? Oh I - I were about twenty-on
e - twenty-one. No - just - nearly about twenty-one, late on in twenties and - they knew I - me mother knew I were courting by doing a bit sick kind of thing, she used to come up our back street you see, at Chorley Old Road and - her mother were a friend 
of my mother's, you see. And say, I - when I got courting like say I' - no money I could always borrow off me mother. Although I'd no need pay me mother back, I could offer it her but she never take it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 You couldn't take her home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, no. No.
 No, I'd be turned twenty - I'd be around - just about twenty-one when I started taking her home and I went in their house first and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280337 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 And yet your mother obviously didn't object to the association?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13700454 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5336029\charrsid14966407 Oh no, but - it were me dad. You see, me dad h
ad not got it broke to him, you see. And then after - me sister - it come up like, I think it were me sister what mentioned like bring her to our house for me tea, I'd been to their house at Sunday and th'old fellow wanted to know why I weren't come home 
